        IT_S_SO_TOUGH_CONSTRUCTING_FRONTIER_STATIONS_IT                               = 7881,  -- It's so tough constructing frontier stations. It's always build, build, build, and scrounge, scrounge, scrounge. All I want is a little break from the monotony of it all.
        IT_S_SO_TOUGH_MAINTAINING_A_FRONTIER_STATION                                  = 7882,  -- It's so tough maintaining a frontier station. I'm always fending off bloodthirsty hellions and scrounging for provisions. All I want is a little break from the monotony of it all.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_LOOK_PLEASED_CRY_A                                           = 7883,  -- What will you do? Look pleased. Cry a river. Act surprised. Rue your life. Cheer. Pretend to be flustered. Blush like a maiden. Rally the troops. Nothing for now.
        AHAHAHA_OF_ALL_THE_THINGS_TO_PULL_I                                           = 7884,  -- Ahahaha! Of all the things to pull, I never thought you'd do that! I had no idea that was coming.
        UM_IS_SOMETHING_THE_MATTER_WITH_YOU_MAYBE                                     = 7885,  -- Um...is something the matter with you? Maybe you should see a physician...
        APPROACHING_FROM_THAT_DIRECTION_AS_FOR_YOUR_GAG                               = 7886,  -- Approaching from that direction [might not have been very effective/was probably the right thing to do.]. As for your gag, [it wasn't with the times/it was right on the mark].
        YOU_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_MUCH_I_NEEDED                                              = 7887,  -- You don't know how much I needed something like that. Thank you.
        FRONTIER_BIVOUAC_IS_PERCENT_WE_ARE_IN_NEED                                    = 7888,  -- [Construction on /]Frontier Bivouac #[1/2/3/4/5] is[/ currently at] # percent [complete/durability]. We are in need of [materials with which to set up camp/provisions], so would it be possible for you to undertake a coalition assignment and assist us in [building this thing/keeping this place running]?
        YOU_CAME_HERE_FROM_A_FARAWAY_LAND_RIGHT                                       = 7889,  -- You came here from a faraway land, right?
        THEN_YOU_CAN_BE_IN_OUR_BRIGADE_YAY                                            = 7890,  -- Then you can be in our brigade! Yay!
        LOOK_YOU_GET_A_NEAT_BADGE_IF_YOU                                              = 7891,  -- Look, you get a neat badge if you join! Oh, but this one's for leaders only. Yours won't be as neat.
        I_KNOW_YOU_WANT_A_BADGE_I_CAN                                                 = 7892,  -- I know you want a badge. I can see it in your eyes. If you want to join, you'll need to show us that special pioneer power!
        IF_YOU_RE_SMART_LIKE_ME_YOU_LL                                                = 7893,  -- If you're smart like me, you'll already know where to get it.
        I_BET_YOU_DON_T_THOUGH_HOW_ABOUT                                              = 7894,  -- I bet you don't, though. How about I give you a hint? Try reeeal hard to remember what that guy said when you registered.
        WH_WH_WHAT_YOU_ALREADY_HAVE_IT                                                = 7895,  -- Wh-wh-what?! You already have it!?
        I_KNEW_THAT_I_WAS_JUST_DOUBLE_TESTING                                         = 7896,  -- ...I knew that! I was just double-testing you!
        WOW_YOU_RE_KIND_OF_DUMB_FOR_AN                                                = 7897,  -- Wow, you're kind of dumb for an adult. Look around the west of Western Adoulin for a woman. If you can't find it with that hint, you don't deserve to be on our force!
        WHAT_DO_YOU_NEED_HON                                                          = 7898,  -- What do you need, hon?
        AH_SO_MERLEG_WANTS_YOU_TO_SHOW_HIM                                            = 7899,  -- Ah, so Merleg wants you to show him the power of an ionis.
        YOU_KNOW_HOW_CHILDREN_ARE_AT_THAT_AGE                                         = 7900,  -- You know how children are at that age. They're just very excited about becoming pioneers and working for certain coalitions. I think it's wonderful that they're showing an interest in their hometown.
        MERLEG_AND_SOME_OF_THE_OTHER_CHILDREN_EVEN                                    = 7901,  -- Merleg and some of the other children even walk around town pretending to keep the city safe. They call themselves the Fantastic Adoulin Imperial Liberators.
        SOMETIMES_WE_HAVE_TO_TELL_THEM_TO_TONE                                        = 7902,  -- Sometimes we have to tell them to tone it down and keep out of trouble, but for the most part--
        OH_MY_WHERE_ARE_MY_MANNERS_YOU_CAME                                           = 7903,  -- Oh, my! Where are my manners? You came to have Ionis cast on you, didn't you?
        MAY_THE_FOUNDER_KING_S_UNDYING_LOVE_PROTECT                                   = 7904,  -- May the founder king's undying love protect you this day!
        NOW_YOU_RE_NOW_OUTFITTED_WITH_AN_IONIS                                        = 7905,  -- Now you're now outfitted with an ionis. Go back and give those children the show of their lives!
        I_CAN_FEEL_A_SPECIAL_POWER_FLOWING_FROM                                       = 7906,  -- I can feel a special power flowing from you. There's no mistaking it--you have Ionis on you!
        I_GUESS_YOU_PASS_WELCOME_TO_THE_FANTASTIC                                     = 7907,  -- I guess you pass. Welcome to the Fantastic Adoulin Imperial Liberators. Here's your neat badge that's not as neat as mine, like I promised.
        SHOW_IT_TO_ANYONE_IN_THE_BRIGADE_AND                                          = 7908,  -- Show it to anyone in the brigade and they'll let you in on our secrets.
        SIGH_THEY_LIKE_TO_RUN_YOU_RAGGED_AT                                           = 7909,  -- <Sigh> They like to run you ragged at the waterfront warehouse.
        HOW_AM_I_SUPPOSED_TO_WORK_WHEN_THEY                                           = 7910,  -- How am I supposed to work when they won't let me eat!?
        I_M_SO_HUNGRY_BUT_I_M_SICK                                                    = 7911,  -- I'm so hungry...but I'm sick of Adoulinian food. It tastes like acuex toxin. I deserve something from the Middle Lands for all my hard work.
        AHA_I_REMEMBER_SOME_GUY_WHO_CAME_BACK                                         = 7912,  -- Aha! I remember some guy who came back from the Middle Lands was talking about %!
        THAT_S_WHAT_I_WANT_CAN_YOU_GET                                                = 7913,  -- That's what I want! Can you get it for me? If I can eat it now before it's widely imported, I can say I liked it before it was popular!
        HURRY_UP_I_WON_T_BE_ABLE_TO                                                   = 7914,  -- Hurry up! I won't be able to move a single step until you bring me %.
        YEEEEEEEEEEEES_YOU_GOT_FOR_ME_AFTER_ALL_THIS                                  = 7915,  -- Yeeeeeeeeeeees! You got % for me! After all this time, I finally have %!
        SNIFF_SNIFF_WHAT_A_DELIGHTFUL_SMELL_I_CAN                                     = 7916,  -- <Sniff, sniff>... What a delightful smell... I can already imagine a matronly figure in an apron slaving over a hot batch of it while the warm Quon sun shines through the window!
        GULP_THIS_S_THE_TASTIEST_THING_THAT_S                                         = 7917,  -- <Gulp>... This's the tastiest thing that's ever passed my lips!
        THE_FLAVOR_S_SO_SIMPLE_BUT_IT_ALSO                                            = 7918,  -- The flavor's so simple...but it also has a mellow backing. All my anger has completely disappeared... I love my job!
        THIS_SINGLE_BOWL_OF_SOUP_HAS_GIVEN_ME                                         = 7919,  -- This single bowl of soup has given me a zest for life! It's even made me nostalgic for Adoulinian food!
        SPEAKING_OF_WHICH_IF_YOU_WANT_A_GOOD                                          = 7920,  -- Speaking of which...if you want a good Ulbukan restaurant, head out of Platea Triumphus towards Big Bridge. I heartily recommend it.
        HEY_THIS_ISN_T_AT_ALL_NO_USE                                                  = 7921,  -- Hey, this isn't % at all... No use letting good food go to waste, though.
        THIS_ISN_T_HALF_BAD_BUT_BRING_ME                                              = 7922,  -- This isn't half bad! But bring me % next time, okay?
        DAMN_IT_WHY_S_IT_GOTTA_BE_NOW                                                 = 7923,  -- Damn it! Why's it gotta be now, of all times!? ...SOS, pioneer! SOS!
        FISH_RE_SWARMIN_ALL_OVER_I_AIN_T                                              = 7924,  -- Fish're swarmin' all over! I ain't never seen so many of 'em in one place before!
        BUT_AS_LUCK_WOULD_HAVE_IT_MY_HARPOON                                          = 7925,  -- But, as luck would have it, my harpoon done broke and it's takin' the wind outta my sails! Maybe I should've been more careful and looked where I was stabbin'...
        I_STILL_GOTS_ME_FAVORITE_HARPOON_HILDA_BUT                                    = 7926,  -- I still gots me favorite harpoon, Hilda, but no way in Davy Jones's locker I'm usin' her in these waters! Normally I'd just drop anchor in the Inventors' Coalition and get them to fix it for me, but...I can't let these fish outta my sight!
        THAT_S_WHERE_YOU_COME_IN_SAILOR                                               = 7927,  -- That's where you come in, sailor.
        COULD_YOU_HELP_AN_OLD_SALT_OUT_AND                                            = 7928,  -- Could you help an old salt out and have them fix this shoddy one for me?
        I_DUNNO_HOW_I_D_REPAY_YOU_BUT                                                 = 7929,  -- I dunno how I'd repay you, but I'm sure I'll think of something while tacklin' these whoppers!
        QUICK_TIME_S_A_WASTIN_THESE_FISH_COULD                                        = 7930,  -- Quick, time's a-wastin'. These fish could be gone any minute! To the Inventors' Coalition with my %, matey!
        IF_YOU_RE_HERE_SEEKING_THE_BRIGHTARUEST_MINDS                                 = 7931,  -- If you're here seeking the brightaruest minds in all of Adoulin, then you're in luck! Welcome to the Inventors' Coalition.
        OR_MAYBE_YOU_VE_COME_TO_GAZE_LONGINGLY                                        = 7932,  -- Or maybe you've come to gaze longingly at me, the best coalition's postaru girl?
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_US_TO_FIXY_WIX_FOR                                              = 7933,  -- What? You want us to fixy-wix % for some fisherman? Hmmm...
        NO_PROBLEM_JUST_BECAUSE_WE_RE_THE_GREATARUEST                                 = 7934,  -- No problem! Just because we're the greataruest coalition around doesn't mean we're above helping townsfolk.
        WE_GET_JOBS_LIKE_THIS_ALL_THE_TIME                                            = 7935,  -- We get jobs like this all the time! I've spruced up tools and tinkered with utensils for citizen-witizens so often that I've lost countaru.
        ALSO_THE_MORE_GOOD_DEEDS_I_DO_THE                                             = 7936,  -- Also, the more good deeds I do, the more popular-wopular I become! I'll have the whole city licking my bootarus soon enough.
        OH_YES_THE_HARPOON                                                            = 7937,  -- ...Oh, yes. The harpoon.
        FIRST_BANG_ON_IT_WITH_SOME_HEAVY_WEAVY                                        = 7938,  -- First, bang on it with some heavy-weavy tools... Next, twistaru until just before the breaking point... ...And there we go. Drumroll please...
        TA_DA_HERE_YOU_ARE_PERFECTLY_RECONSTRUCTARUED                                 = 7939,  -- Ta-da! Here you are, perfectly reconstructarued!
        WELL_ACTUALLY_IT_SHOULD_BE_BETTER_THAN_BEFORE                                 = 7940,  -- Well, actually, it should be better than before. I enhanced its durability so it'll last multiple-wultiple times as long.
        SINCE_I_M_SO_GENEROUS_WENEROUS_I_ALSO                                         = 7941,  -- Since I'm so generous-wenerous, I also took the liberty of adding a button that makes it expand and retract. I'm just that selfless.
        NO_NEED_TO_THANK_ME_YOUR_LOVE_AND                                             = 7942,  -- No need to thank me. Your love and adoration should prove more than sufficientaru.
        I_SEE_THE_INVENTORS_COALITION_DONE_LIVED_UP                                   = 7943,  -- I see the Inventors' Coalition done lived up to their reputation once again!
        THEY_VE_BAILED_ME_OUT_SO_MUCH_OVER                                            = 7944,  -- They've bailed me out so much over the years--especially that kind Tarutaru girl. She may seem shallower than the Zoldeff durin' a drought, but she's got a heart larger'n an orobon's maw.
        I_AIN_T_GOT_MUCH_TO_RETURN_THE                                                = 7945,  -- I ain't got much to return the favor with, but I always try to give 'em some of my catch when I can. I know how int'restin' them books and all can be, but sometimes you need to stuff some food down your gullet.
        PLUS_THE_LAST_THING_I_BE_NEEDIN_IS                                            = 7946,  -- Plus, the last thing I be needin' is for them to faint from hunger when my tools give out.
        EH_WHAT_BE_THIS_BUTTON_HERE_WHOA_IT                                           = 7947,  -- Eh? What be this button here? Whoa...it just got longer than a jagil's maw all by itself!
        UGH_I_ALWAYS_TELL_EM_THEY_DON_T                                               = 7948,  -- Ugh...I always tell 'em they don't need to include all this weird stuff.
        I_PPRECIATE_THE_THOUGHT_BUT_WHEN_THE_BIG                                      = 7949,  -- I 'ppreciate the thought, but when the big one bites, you want somethin' you're used to, not some newfangled whatsamajigger.
        THEY_AIN_T_MEAN_BAD_BY_IT_SO                                                  = 7950,  -- They ain't mean bad by it, so I guess I can't complain...
        WELL_IF_ANYTHING_ELSE_HAPPENS_TO_ME_I                                         = 7951,  -- Well, if anything else happens to me, I'll be on the lookout for you!
        WHADDYA_WANT                                                                  = 7952,  -- Whaddya want?
        I_DON_T_HAVE_TIME_FOR_LOUSES_LIKE                                             = 7953,  -- I don't have time for louses like y...
        WAIT_A_MINUTE_YOU_SEEM_LIKE_YOU_HAVE                                          = 7954,  -- Wait a minute. You seem like you have time on your hands. Why don't I give you some wholesome work? None of this stirring-up-trouble-in-the-jungle stuff.
        THE_GUARD_ON_DUTY_TODAY_FELL_ASLEEP_BEFORE                                    = 7955,  -- The guard on duty today fell asleep before his patrol, that laggard. Take this paper with his route on it and fill in for him. You've got nothing better to do, right?
        FOLLOW_THOSE_INSTRUCTIONS_TO_THE_LETTER_THEY_SHOULDN                          = 7956,  -- Follow those instructions to the letter. They shouldn't be hard to figure out, even for an outsider like you.
        I_THOUGHT_I_SENT_YOU_OUT_ON_PATROL                                            = 7957,  -- I thought I sent you out on patrol! Are you purposefully trying to scare our people? Now go!
        AH_HOW_ARE_YOU_TODAY                                                          = 7958,  -- Ah, %! How are you today?
        OH_YOU_RE_ON_PATROL_FOR_THE_PEACEKEEPERS                                      = 7959,  -- Oh, you're on patrol for the Peacekeepers' Coalition? Nice to see you giving back to the community.
        THERE_S_NOTHING_OF_NOTE_WHATSOEVER_AROUND_HERE                                = 7960,  -- There's nothing of note whatsoever around here, and the colonization effort is proceeding just fine. Thank you so much for checking in.
        I_KNOW_SOME_PEOPLE_ARE_OPPOSED_TO_WHAT                                        = 7961,  -- I know some people are opposed to what we do, while others are terrified of the risks involved, but I hope you won't mind taking assignments from the Pioneers' Coalition sometime.
        HI_THERE_WELCOME_TO_THE_COURIERS_COALITION                                    = 7962,  -- Hi there... Welcome to the Couriers' Coalition.
        WHAT_YOU_RE_MAKING_ROUNDS_TO_SEE_HOW                                          = 7963,  -- What? You're making rounds...to see how things are...?
        NO_NEED_TO_WORRY_ABOUT_US_IT_S                                                = 7964,  -- No need to worry...about us. It's all going...well. Shipments to the coalitions...are okay. Shipments to the frontier...are okay.
        W_WE_HAVE_ALL_THE_LOCAL_DELIVERIES_UM                                         = 7965,  -- W-we have all the local deliveries, um, covered. But we always ask p-pioneers to, er, transport jungle-bound cargo. I h-hope you'll...you know, help us out with that stuff...in the future.
        ANYTHING_REMOTELY_IMPORTANT_TO_LIFE_IN_ADOULIN_OR                             = 7966,  -- Anything remotely important to life in Adoulin or pioneering winds up in this warehouse. Why do you want to know?
        AH_SO_YOU_RE_FILLING_IN_FOR_THE                                               = 7967,  -- Ah, so you're filling in for the regular patrolman. No wonder he hadn't come by yet.
        ANYWAY_NO_PROBLEMS_ON_THE_ADOULIN_WATERFRONT                                  = 7968,  -- Anyway, no problems on the Adoulin Waterfront.
        STOP_DAWDLING_AND_GO_HELP_SOME_PEOPLE_WHO                                     = 7969,  -- Stop dawdling and go help some people who need it. All I require is more time to carry all these provisions.
        OH_AND_DON_T_EVER_COME_HERE_AT                                                = 7970,  -- Oh, and don't ever come here at night! I don't care how beautiful you think the scenery is.
        ESPECIALLY_NOT_WITH_YOUR_GIRLFRIEND_BOYFRIEND_IF_YOU                          = 7971,  -- Especially not with your girlfriend/boyfriend]! If you don't want to sleep with the fishes, you'll take that to heart.
        PERFORMING_RANDOM_ACTS_OF_KINDNESS_FOR_ADOULINIANS_AGAIN                      = 7972,  -- Performing random acts of kindness for Adoulinians again? How thoughtful.
        ON_ONE_HAND_I_M_SORRY_WE_DON                                                  = 7973,  -- On one hand, I'm sorry we don't have any work for you. On the other, it's a relief that all's well.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_NOTICED_THE_FOUNTAIN_HERE_IN                                    = 7974,  -- Have you ever noticed the fountain here in Platea Triumphus? It's named Fontis Xanira, after one of the knights who fought beside the founder king against the continent's evil forces.
        THOUGH_THE_ORIGIN_OF_ITS_NAME_MAY_SEEM                                        = 7975,  -- Though the origin of its name may seem imposing, today people come here to take a load off.
        THE_NEXT_TIME_YOU_COME_BY_ON_PATROL                                           = 7976,  -- The next time you come by on patrol, how about resolving some residents' disputes with me? Oh, and I'm always willing to lend an ear should you feel lonely.
        IF_YOU_RE_HERE_SEEKING_THE_BRIGHTARUEST_MINDS_2                               = 7977,  -- If you're here seeking the brightaruest minds in all of Adoulin, then you're in luck! Welcome to the Inventors' Coalition.
        OR_MAYBE_YOU_VE_COME_TO_GAZE_LONGINGLY_2                                      = 7978,  -- Or maybe you've come to gaze longingly at me, the best coalition's postaru girl?
        ON_PATROL_YOU_SAY_LET_ME_THINK_DO                                             = 7979,  -- On patrol, you say? Let me think. Do we have any tasky-wasks that require your assistance...?
        WE_RE_CURRENTLY_WORKING_ON_ALL_THE_GADGETARUS                                 = 7980,  -- We're currently working on all the gadgetarus in need of repair, that fertilizer has been sent to the Civic Arboretum, and I believe our research into Mog Garden construction is progressing-wessing well.
        THE_ONLY_THING_I_CAN_THINK_OF_IS                                              = 7981,  -- The only thing I can think of is how we sometimes run out of materials. We wouldn't have to worry if you'd take some assignmentarus from us, though. You know, the more jobs you undertake, the more you get to see wonderful little me.
        THE_FERRY_THAT_DOCKS_HERE_TRANSPORTS_PIONEERS_TO                              = 7982,  -- The ferry that docks here transports pioneers to the chain of small islands that compose the Adoulinian residential area.
        I_DOUBT_YOU_INTEND_TO_UTILIZE_IT_WHILE                                        = 7983,  -- I doubt you intend to utilize it while you are on patrol, but feel free to follow your desires and board at any time.
        AS_FOR_POSSIBLE_PROBLEMS_WE_ARE_NOT_EXPERIENCING                              = 7984,  -- As for possible problems, we are not experiencing any currently. Every vessel is on schedule and the seas are calm.
        OH_AND_SHOULD_YOU_EVER_WISH_TO_VISIT                                          = 7985,  -- Oh, and should you ever wish to visit the residential area, simply pass through this arch and descend the steps to the dock. That is all, sir/ma'am].
        WE_RE_ALWAYS_GLAD_TO_HAVE_PEOPLE_COME                                         = 7986,  -- We're always glad to have people come inside the Mummers' Coalition!
        HEY_I_JUST_MADE_UP_A_THEME_SONG                                               = 7987,  -- Hey, I just made up a theme song for us! Want to hear it? I love fun, fun loves me, we're--t Oh, you're on patrol... Sorry.
        ADOULIN_S_FINEST_HAVE_NOTHING_TO_WORRY_ABOUT                                  = 7988,  -- Adoulin's finest have nothing to worry about. All the people here are happy and content.t
        WE_TRY_OUR_BEST_TO_HAVE_EVERYONE_IN                                           = 7989,  -- We try our best to have everyone in the city get the most out of life. We hold grand events, cheer soldiers up on the battlefield, and constantly cook up new ways to entertain Adoulinians! Come get some assignments from us if you want to see more of what we're about.
        OOOR_DROP_BY_AND_PLAY_ONE_OF_OUR                                              = 7990,  -- ...Ooor drop by and play one of our games the next time you want to have some fun.t
        FINALLY_FINISHED_HUH_NO_ONE_WAS_TROUBLED_BY                                   = 7991,  -- Finally finished, huh? ...No one was troubled by anything? Good.
        SPEAKING_OF_TROUBLE_EVERYONE_IN_THE_PEACEKEEPERS_COALITION                    = 7992,  -- Speaking of trouble, everyone in the Peacekeepers' Coalition makes ridding our city of it their number one priority! There's no room for those who can't follow this mantra. That's why we'll be punishing the person you replaced today.
        PATROLLING_THE_STREETS_IS_NOT_OUR_ONLY_TACTIC                                 = 7993,  -- Patrolling the streets is not our only tactic. We also look out upon Adoulin from guard towers and the city walls. If we see any fires of discontent, we snuff them out!
        SHOULD_MONSTERS_SOMEHOW_BREACH_JORIUS_YETT_WE_LL                              = 7994,  -- Should monsters somehow breach Jorius Yett, we'll be there to stop them, too.
        SEE_WE_HAVE_ENOUGH_PROBLEMS_WITHOUT_HAVING_TO                                 = 7995,  -- See, we have enough problems without having to deal with pioneers. Watch your step around this town, or we might just have to deal with you.
        WHAT_EXCELLENT_TIMING_I_AM_LOATH_TO_IMPOSE                                    = 7996,  -- What excellent timing! I am loath to impose, but I require your assistance.
        IT_IS_SUCH_A_BLIGHT_ON_MY_SPOTLESS                                            = 7997,  -- It is such a blight on my spotless record that I hesitate to even explain why I must seek your aid...but it is inevitable.
        I_I_DID_NOT_EXERCISE_THE_APPROPRIATE_AMOUNT                                   = 7998,  -- I...I did not exercise the appropriate amount of caution, and we have received the wrong supplies.
        THE_ITEM_IN_QUESTION_STILL_REMAINS_IN_MY                                      = 7999,  -- The item in question still remains in my possession, but I have not the time to rectify this error myself. Would you be so kind as to deliver it to the warehouse at the Adoulin Waterfront for me?
        PASSING_IT_OFF_TO_THE_SUPERVISOR_THERE_WILL                                   = 8000,  -- Passing it off to the supervisor there will be sufficient. It is his job to transport it to the assigned location.
        GODDESS_SPEED_YOU_PIONEER                                                     = 8001,  -- Goddess speed you, pioneer.
        WHAT_THE_WRONG_DESTINATION_SIGH_I_HATE_WHEN                                   = 8002,  -- What!? The wrong destination!? ...<Sigh> I hate when this happens.
        GIMME_THAT_UH_HUH_LOOKS_LIKE_THIS_WAS                                         = 8003,  -- Gimme that...uh-huh... Looks like this was originally bound for C-6 in the Rala Waterways.
        TAKE_THE_ROAD_UP_THAT_HILL_OVER_THERE                                         = 8004,  -- Take the road up that hill over there and you'll find another street that leads to them. Take a right once you're inside and you'll come to a sluice gate.
        PUT_IT_DOWN_NEAR_THERE_IT_S_AN                                                = 8005,  -- Put it down near there. It's an important package, too, so I'll curse you to your grave if someone sees you down there. What? I don't care what that Elvaan said. I don't have the time to deal with lost packages.
        I_HAVE_BEEN_INFORMED_THAT_THE_PACKAGE_MADE                                    = 8006,  -- I have been informed that the package made it to its destination safely. Thank you so much.
        I_KNOW_FULL_WELL_THAT_SUCH_MISTAKES_ARE                                       = 8007,  -- I know full well that such mistakes are a common occurrence, but I cannot help but feel the crushing weight of failure upon my shoulders whenever confronted with such situations. The saving grace of it all is that nothing happened to the package.
        FROM_NOW_ON_I_PLEDGE_TO_BE_EVEN                                               = 8008,  -- From now on, I pledge to be even more involved in the supervision of Couriers' Coalition members.
        MY_APOLOGIES_I_HAVE_ALREADY_SQUANDERED_SO_MUCH                                = 8009,  -- My apologies. I have already squandered so much of your precious time. I shall waste no more with trivial banter.
        FARE_THEE_WELL_PIONEER                                                        = 8010,  -- Fare thee well, pioneer.
        GOOD_WORK_EVERYTHING_S_IN_ORDER_NOW_SHOVE                                     = 8011,  -- Good work. Everything's in order. Now shove it.
        WE_HAVEN_T_GIVEN_UP_JUST_YET_WE                                               = 8012,  -- We haven't given up just yet. We just need to bide our time, that's all.
        THANKS_FOR_THAT_EARLIER                                                       = 8013,  -- Thanks for that % earlier.
        PHEW_MY_THROAT_SURE_IS_DRY_THOUGH                                             = 8014,  -- Phew, my throat sure is dry, though...
        HEY_HEY_HEY_DON_T_BE_LIKE_THAT                                                = 8015,  -- Hey, hey, hey! Don't be like that! We're the bestest of all friends for eternity, remember?
        AND_SINCE_YOU_RE_SUCH_A_GOOD_FRIEND                                           = 8016,  -- And since you're such a good friend, I know you'll want to surprise me. Get me a drink made from something that'll knock my tunic off!
        I_CAN_T_WAIT_TO_GET_MY_LIQUID                                                 = 8017,  -- I can't wait to get my liquid gift. You're such a good friend, %.
        HEY_I_THOUGHT_YOU_WERE_GOING_TO_SURPRISE                                      = 8018,  -- Hey, I thought you were going to surprise me with a drink. I'm going to shrivel into a skeleton if you don't hurry up!
        YEEEEEEEEES_SUCH_AN_GULP_INTENSE_AROMA_SO_THIS                                = 8019,  -- Yeeeeeeeees! Such an...<gulp>...intense aroma... So this is the fabled %...
        IF_THIS_IS_MADE_BY_GOBLINS_I_BEST                                             = 8020,  -- If this is made by Goblins...I best prepare my stomach...
        EW_IT_SMELLS_LIKE_RAW_FISH_BUT_I                                              = 8021,  -- Ew...it smells like raw fish! But...I asked for it...so here goes nothing!
        GLUG_GLUK_GULP_BLEEEEEECH_IT_TASTES_LIKE_BILGE                                = 8022,  -- <Glug>...<gluk>...<gulp>... Bleeeeeech, it tastes like bilge water! Get it away from me!
        MY_TONGUE_S_COATED_IN_IT_YUCK_I                                               = 8023,  -- My tongue's coated in it. Yuck, I feel it crawling down my throat! Oh no, I can even smell it when I open my mouth!
        HAAAH_HAAAH_HAAAH_I_DON_T_THINK_YOU                                           = 8024,  -- Haaah...haaah...haaah... I don't think you want to drink that. Instead, try the caf%i across Big Bridge in one of Eastern Adoulin's plazas.
        IT_S_TOO_HOITY_TOITY_FOR_MY_TASTES                                            = 8025,  -- It's too hoity-toity for my tastes, but I just may have to go there anyway... I need to cleanse my palate.
        THIS_ISN_T_MUCH_OF_A_SURPRISE_IT                                              = 8026,  -- This isn't much of a surprise. It's so...normal.
        HEY_THIS_IS_KIND_OF_TASTY_TOO_BAD                                             = 8027,  -- Hey, this is kind of tasty! Too bad it's not what I'm looking for. You'll need to bring me something else, buddy.
        WE_VE_SHARED_SO_MANY_MEMORIES_TOGETHER_HAVEN                                  = 8028,  -- We've shared so many memories together, haven't we? Like the time you gave me that %. I had to curl up on the ground for hours before I stopped feeling sick.
        BUT_ANYWAY_THE_LITTLE_CHOCOBO_WHO_TOLD_ME                                     = 8029,  -- But anyway... The little chocobo who told me about % recently chirped to me about a pink beverage.
        APPARENTLY_THE_LIQUID_INSIDE_IS_HERETICAL_OR_SOMETHING                        = 8030,  -- Apparently the liquid inside is heretical or something, and bizarre stuff happens to your body when you drink it!
        I_VE_GOTTA_HAVE_ONE_I_MUST_EXPERIENCE                                         = 8031,  -- I've gotta have one! I must experience its effects firsthand!
        HA_NICE_TRY_THAT_FACE_WON_T_WORK                                              = 8032,  -- Ha, nice try. That face won't work on me. I've seen it too many times already.
        MAKE_SURE_IT_S_THE_PINK_ONE_THAT                                              = 8033,  -- Make sure it's the pink one that's sparkling. Sparkling and pink, okay? Okay!
        IF_YOU_DON_T_GET_ME_THAT_SPARKLING                                            = 8034,  -- If you don't get me that sparkling pink drink, I'm gonna go tear you limb from limb like a Velkk marauder, buddy.
        YEEEEEEEEES_IT_S_PINK_IT_S_SPARKLY_IT                                         = 8035,  -- Yeeeeeeeees! It's pink...it's sparkly...it's <gulp> exactly what I asked for!
        GLUG_HM_IT_GOES_DOWN_SMOOTHER_THAN_PUGIL                                      = 8036,  -- <Glug>...hm? ...It goes down smoother than pugil roe! Oh, and there's the slightest bite to it that brings out its sweetness. I love it!
        ACK_BY_THE_FOUNDER_KING_THE_PAIN_CONSUMES                                     = 8037,  -- Ack! By the founder king, the pain consumes my soul! Altana, forgive me my trespasses...!
        SO_THE_RUMORS_WERE_TRUE_IT_IS_CURSED                                          = 8038,  -- So the rumors were true! It is cursed! ...%, when will my body stop shaking?
        MAYBE_GETTING_BACK_TO_WORK_WILL_MAKE_ME                                       = 8039,  -- Maybe getting back to work will make me forget how disgusting I feel...
        THIS_ISN_T_VERY_PINK_AND_DOESN_T                                              = 8040,  -- This isn't very pink and doesn't sparkle...but oh well.
        NOT_BAD_NEXT_TIME_BRING_ME_A_SPARKLING                                        = 8041,  -- Not bad! Next time, bring me a sparkling pink one, friend of friends. And make it snappy!
        HEY_THIS_IS_THE_SAME_DRINK_FROM_BEFORE                                        = 8042,  -- Hey, this is the same drink from before! Fool me once, shame on me. Fool me twice...well, you're not gonna fool me twice!
        I_WANT_THE_ONE_THAT_S_PINK_AND                                                = 8043,  -- I want the one that's pink and sparkling! Pink and shiny, I say!
        MAIN_MENU_QUEST_FLAGS_KEY_ITEMS                                               = 8044,  -- Main Menu Quest flags. Key items.
        QUEST_FLAGS_BACK_ALL_OPERATION_UNVERIFIED                                     = 8045,  -- Quest flags Back. All (operation unverified).
        QUEST_FLAG_OPERATION_BACK_ZERO_CLEAR                                          = 8046,  -- Quest flag operation Back. Zero clear.
        KEY_ITEMS_BACK_ALL_OPERATION_UNVERIFIED                                       = 8047,  -- Key items Back. All (operation unverified).
        SELCT_KEY_ITEM_BACK_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE                                   = 8048,  -- Selct key item. Back. Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. NExt page.
        KEY_ITEMS_OPERATION_BACK_DELETE_ALL                                           = 8049,  -- Key items operation Back. Delete all.
        ID_8050                                                                       = 8050,  -- [Quests reset to initial settings/Key items reset to initial settings/All flags reset].
        GOOD_DAY_TO_YOU_ADVENTURER_HAVE_YOU_REGISTERED                                = 8051,  -- Good day to you, adventurer! Have you registered with the Pioneers' Coalition yet? If not, I strongly recommend you take the time to do so at your earliest convenience!
        ANOTHER_DAY_ANOTHER_DISTRACTION_ADVENTURER_WOULD_YOU_LIKE                     = 8052,  -- Another day, another distraction, adventurer! Would you like to learn more about this splendiferous machine here?
        ANY_INTEREST_IN_THE_DEVICE_YOU_BETCHA_NOT                                     = 8053,  -- Any interest in the device? You betcha! Not particularly.
        AWW_AND_I_HAD_MY_SCRIPT_ALL_PLANNED                                           = 8054,  -- Aww, and I had my script all planned out, too! If you ever change your mind, you know where to find me!
        THIS_IS_A_MAGICAL_APPARATUS_REFERRED_TO_AS                                    = 8055,  -- This is a magical apparatus referred to as a waypoint. You can use it to instantaneously teleport to anywhere in Western Adoulin.
        OH_HO_FORGIVE_ME_FOR_BABYING_YOU_OF                                           = 8056,  -- Oh ho, forgive me for babying you. Of course you know that much--you probably used one to get here!
        AS_YOU_CAN_IMAGINE_IT_S_QUITE_A                                               = 8057,  -- As you can imagine, it's quite a convenient little invention, but I'd only try going places you've visited before, if I were you.
        MUTTER_SOME_IDIOTS_TRY_TO_GO_PLACES_THEY                                      = 8058,  -- <Mutter> Some idiots try to go places they've never heard of and get their heads all turned around...
        OOPS_LOOKS_LIKE_MY_INNER_MONOLOGUE_SLIPPED_OUT                                = 8059,  -- Oops--looks like my inner monologue slipped out again. I'm sure you can imagine what a pain it must be to guide the lost back home. Twaha!
        ALL_JOKING_ASIDE_IF_YOU_DON_T_HAVE                                            = 8060,  -- All joking aside, if you don't have % attuned to where you want to go, the thing just won't work!
        MORE_PRECISELY_IT_S_NOT_THE_LOCATION_ITSELF                                   = 8061,  -- More precisely, it's not the location itself so much as the magnetic fields located there. So, to make things more convenient in the long run, you'll want to walk from place to place and attune your %.
        ONCE_IT_S_ATTUNED_YOU_RE_FREE_TO                                              = 8062,  -- Once it's attuned, you're free to zip around as you please. So why dillydally? Let's get started with this one right here!
        THAT_WASN_T_A_SUGGESTION_MORE_OF_AN                                           = 8063,  -- That wasn't a suggestion. More of an order. Well, order might be a bit harsh. Maybe request? Yes, let's go with request.
        SEE_NOW_YOU_RE_PLAYING_WITH_PORTALS_BUT                                       = 8064,  -- See? Now you're playing with portals! But seriously--you'll save yourself a lot of headaches down the road if you just get it over with now.
        WHAT_S_THIS_YOU_VE_ATTUNED_TO_THIS                                            = 8065,  -- What's this? You've attuned to this spot already? Gee, you're quicker on the uptake than I'd have thought!
        THE_PIONEER_WAY_OF_LIFE_IS_DIFFICULT_ENOUGH                                   = 8066,  -- The pioneer way of life is difficult enough without having to worry about travel, so we set up these waypoints to make things as easy as possible.
        HUT_TUT_YOUR_TASK_ISN_T_DONE_YET                                              = 8067,  -- Hut-tut! Your task isn't done yet! Find those waypoints! Gotta attune 'em all!
        LET_ME_SEE_THAT_THING_MAYBE_I_CAN                                             = 8068,  -- Let me see that thing. Maybe I can tell you which waypoints remain.
        THE_CENTER_OF_WESTERN_ADOULIN_THAT_WOULD_BE                                   = 8069,  -- The center of Western Adoulin. That would be...right here! The place you're looking for is just in front of the Couriers' Coalition in Platea Triumphus.
        I_M_SURE_YOU_CAN_SEE_IT_FROM                                                  = 8070,  -- I'm sure you can see it from here--that weird...no, unique...fountain over in that plaza? It's right there!
        JUST_NORTH_OF_PLATEA_TRIUMPHUS_NEAR_THE_AIRSHIPS                              = 8071,  -- Just north of Platea Triumphus, near the airships. That's not so bad, right?
        THIS_ONE_S_LOCATED_FAAAR_AWAY_AT_THE                                          = 8072,  -- This one's located faaar away at the northern edges of Western Adoulin. My calves are burning just thinking about walking there! Well...that's what the waypoints are for!
        HEAD_NORTH_PAST_PLATEA_TRIUMPHUS_BUT_DON_T                                    = 8073,  -- Head north past Platea Triumphus. But don't go too far, or you'll reach the airship docks. There's this downward slope on your left along the way. That's your target!
        BY_THE_WATERFRONT_JUST_DOWN_THAT_SLOPE_WHAT                                   = 8074,  -- By the waterfront, just down that slope. What would a city known for maritime trading be without a bustling waterfront?
        HEAD_STRAIGHT_EAST_FROM_PLATEA_TRIUMPHUS_THERE_S                              = 8075,  -- Head straight east from Platea Triumphus. There's one located just in front of Big Bridge. If you're feeling adventurous, you can cross the bridge to reach Eastern Adoulin, where the castle is.
        HMM_TAKE_THE_STREETS_TO_THE_SOUTHWEST_OF                                      = 8076,  -- Hmm...take the streets to the southwest of Platea Triumphus to find this one. It's located just in front of the auction house. Promise me you won't spend all your gil when you get there, hm? After all that work you did to get here in the first place...
        LET_S_SEE_THERE_S_ONE_LOCATED_TO                                              = 8077,  -- Let's see. There's one located to the south of Platea Triumphus. It's where the Rent-a-Rooms await for all your adventuring needs. Come to think of it, why are you asking me this? You mean you haven't even been there yet!?
        THIS_ONE_IS_LOCATED_SOUTHEAST_OF_PLATEA_TRIUMPHUS                             = 8078,  -- This one is located southeast of Platea Triumphus. You'll find there the pride and joy of all Adoulin--the Inventors' Coalition. The road runs pretty deep there, so make sure you can find your way back out! I don't want to have to come get you!
        SOUTH_OF_PLATEA_TRIUMPHUS_THAT_ONE_YOU_LL                                     = 8079,  -- South of Platea Triumphus, that one. You'll want to turn right along the path to the Mog Resort. You should pop by the Mummers' Coalition--that's your goal! Might as well catch some R&R while you're there, too!
        SO_HEY_CONGRATULATIONS_ON_GETTING_ALL_THE_WAYPOINTS                           = 8080,  -- So hey, congratulations on getting all the waypoints! I won't say you set a world record for speed, but it is what it is. This should make your travels through Adoulin a breeze!
        BY_THE_BY_HAVE_YOU_HEARD_OF_THIS                                              = 8081,  -- By the by, have you heard of this guy Anastase?
        THAT_OLD_FART_WELL_PERHAPS_I_SHOULD_BE                                        = 8082,  -- That old fart--well, perhaps I should be respectful, because he IS my grandfather--was treated with great love and care by the people of the Middle Lands. I know you probably didn't have anything to do with that, but I just wanted to let you know how grateful I am for the kindness of your people.
        HEY_HOW_GOES_THE_WHOLE_PIONEERING_THING_YOU                                   = 8083,  -- Hey, how goes the whole pioneering thing? You making sure to use those waypoints? Things are tough enough out there, so no reason to make life harder on yourself!
        YOU_ADJUSTED_THE_WAYPOINT_WITH_YOUR_2                                         = 8084,  -- You adjusted the waypoint with your %.
        THERE_APPEAR_TO_BE_NO_ANOMALIES_WITH_THIS                                     = 8085,  -- There appear to be no anomalies with this waypoint.
        YOU_THERE_COME_TO_GET_A_TASTE_OF                                              = 8086,  -- You there! Come to get a taste of our famous cuisine?
        I_D_LOVE_TO_GIVE_YA_THE_HOUSE                                                 = 8087,  -- I'd love to give ya the house special, but hey--it's so popular that I'm completely out of ingredients to make it!
        WAIT_YER_ONE_OF_THEM_PIONEERS_AIN_T                                           = 8088,  -- Wait...yer one of them pioneers, ain't ya? Tell ya what. You bring me some more ingredients and I'll whip up something really good.
        HOW_ABOUT_IT_GUY_LITTLE_LADY                                                  = 8089,  -- How about it, guy/little lady]?
        LEND_A_HAND_SURE_FOOD_SOUNDS_GOOD_I                                           = 8090,  -- Lend a hand? Sure. Food sounds good. I've got better things to do.
        TOO_BAD_MAYBE_LATER_THEN                                                      = 8091,  -- Too bad. Maybe later, then.
        YER_A_REAL_PAL_HERE_S_WHAT_I                                                  = 8092,  -- Yer a real pal! Here's what I need: # %, %, and %.
        BRING_ME_THOSE_AND_I_LL_MAKE_A                                                = 8093,  -- Bring me those and I'll make a shell-shocking dish like none ya ever seen!
        AND_BRING_ME_THOSE_AND_I_LL_BE                                                = 8094,  -- # %, %, and %. Bring me those, and I'll be able to make ya somethin' special.
        GOTTA_LOVE_THAT_PIONEER_DEPENDABILITY                                         = 8095,  -- Gotta love that pioneer dependability.
        HANG_ON_JUST_A_TICK_TOGETHER_WITH_WHAT                                        = 8096,  -- Hang on just a tick. Together with what you've brought me, we add some %, %, %, and %. Plus, ya gotta heat it up just right. Not too strong, not too weak.
        AAAND_WE_RE_DONE_MY_FAMOUS_BET_YER                                            = 8097,  -- Aaand, we're done. My famous %. Bet yer mouth's startin' to water just lookin' at it!
        IT_S_ON_THE_HOUSE_AFTER_ALL_YER                                               = 8098,  -- It's on the house. After all, yer the one who brought me what I needed, and it was fun bein' able to make some again.
        OH_HO_MADE_SOME_YERSELF_DID_YA_I                                              = 8099,  -- Oh-ho, made some yerself, did ya? I'm impressed.
        BUT_I_REALLY_WANTED_TO_DON_THE_OL                                             = 8100,  -- But I really wanted to don the ol' chef's hat for this one. If ya get more ingredients, make sure to bring 'em, back to me.
        WHY_HELLO_THERE_HERE_TO_SEE_THE_LOVELIEST                                     = 8101,  -- Why, hello there. Here to see the loveliest lady of the Inventors' Coalition?
        NO_THE_CIVIC_ARBORETUM_SENT_YOU_AHA_YOU                                       = 8102,  -- No? ...The Civic Arboretum sent you? Aha--you must be after some %, then.
        I_M_STUCK_AT_MY_POST_THANKS_TO                                                = 8103,  -- I'm stuck at my post thanks to Amchuchu, so since you're here, mind delivering this for me? It's my own special creation.
        BUT_WILL_VEGETABLES_GROWN_USING_REALLY_BE_SAFE                                = 8104,  -- But will vegetables grown using % really be safe to use? I mean, aren't the ones grown by Mother Nature herself the tastiest of all?
        OH_I_M_NOT_ATTACKING_THE_CIVIC_ARBORETUM                                      = 8105,  -- Oh, I'm not attacking the Civic Arboretum. Please don't take it that way.
        IF_IT_WEREN_T_FOR_THEM_PEOPLE_IN                                              = 8106,  -- If it weren't for them, people in the slums might have to go hungry.
        I_CAN_VOUCH_FOR_THE_QUALITY_OF_THESE                                          = 8107,  -- I can vouch for the quality of these %. I would never give them anything that didn't have my seal of approval.
        A_GOOD_DAY_TO_YOU_GOOD_SIR_MADAM                                              = 8108,  -- A good day to you, good sir/madam]. Have you found the waypoints useful in your pioneering activities? They have been set up for your convenience, so do not hesitate to use them as you see fit.
        WHILE_I_HAVE_YOUR_ATTENTION_HAVE_I_TOLD                                       = 8109,  -- While I have your attention--have I told you of my most oppressive grandfather, who is working with the waypoints in the Middle Lands?
        THE_OLD_COOT_WILL_NOT_BE_BACK_FOR                                             = 8110,  -- The old coot will not be back for a while, so naturally I am worried about his well-being. Can I ask a small favor of you?
        LISTEN_TO_HER_STORY_SURE_I_VE_GOT                                             = 8111,  -- Listen to her story? Sure. I've got better things to do.
        I_SEE_I_SUPPOSE_YOU_HAVE_NO_REASON                                            = 8112,  -- I see. I suppose you have no reason to help me, but...if you ever change your mind, I will be here waiting.
        YOU_HAVE_MY_THANKS_I_HAVE_PREPARED_SOME                                       = 8113,  -- You have my thanks. I have prepared some traditional Adoulinian cuisine for him, as he must surely miss the fine taste of his homeland.
        I_AM_ALSO_INTERESTED_IN_HEARING_HOW_THOSE                                     = 8114,  -- I am also interested in hearing how those odd fellows--his surveying party, that is--are getting along. You see, their families are stricken with worry, and I made a promise to check up on them.
        YOUR_AID_IS_GREATLY_APPRECIATED_OH_DEAR_I                                     = 8115,  -- Your aid is greatly appreciated. Oh dear--I forgot to tell you my grandfather's name: Anastase.
        MY_DEAR_PIONEER_I_HAVE_COOKED_UP_A                                            = 8116,  -- My dear pioneer, I have cooked up a lovely Adoulinian meal for my grandfather. Could I trouble you to bring it to him?
        DELIVER_A_MEAL_FOR_HER_IN_A_JIFFY                                             = 8117,  -- Deliver a meal for her? In a jiffy! Sorry. Too busy.
        I_KNOW_THIS_MAY_SOUND_RUDE_BUT_PLEASE                                         = 8118,  -- I know this may sound rude, but please do be careful with this dish, for I put all my familial love into cooking it.
        MY_GRANDFATHER_AND_HIS_ENTOURAGE_ARE_DOING_WELL                               = 8119,  -- My grandfather and his entourage are doing well? This is wonderful news, indeed. My gratitude knows no bounds.
        I_CAN_NEVER_STOP_WORRYING_ABOUT_HIM_SO                                        = 8120,  -- I can never stop worrying about him, so I might ask you to bring some more of my home cooking to him later--if you are free, that is.
        NO_SHARURU_THAT_HUSSY_OH_SHE_SENT_YOU                                         = 8121,  -- No? Sharuru? That hussy? Oh--she sent you here. I see. Then you must be interested in the %.
        ONE_MOMENT_A_LITTLE_TWEAK_HERE_A_COUPLE                                       = 8122,  -- One moment. A little tweak here... A couple adjustments there... ...Yes. This will do nicely.
        THERE_YOU_GO_THIS_SHOULD_HELP_YOU_FIX                                         = 8123,  -- There you go--%. This should help you fix those waypoints right up!
        EXCUSE_ME_MISTER_MA_AM_IS_THAT_A                                              = 8124,  -- Excuse me, mister/ma'am]--is that a Fantastic Adoulin Imperial Liberators badge I see?
        I_M_CLAUTAIRE_I_JUST_JOINED_THE_LIBERATORS                                    = 8125,  -- I'm Clautaire! I just joined the Liberators a couple days ago!
        I_WANNA_BE_A_PIONEER_JUST_LIKE_YOU                                            = 8126,  -- I wanna be a pioneer just like you someday, but my parents say I have to go to school first to learn more about the world.
        FOR_ONE_OF_MY_CLASS_PROJECTS_I_M                                              = 8127,  -- For one of my class projects I'm studying about Adoulin's soil quality. Sounds fun, doesn't it?
        BUT_IT_S_NOT_EASY_I_NEED_BUT                                                  = 8128,  -- But it's not easy. I need %, but I can't get hold of one myself...
        BUT_IF_YOU_RE_A_PIONEER_IT_MUST                                               = 8129,  -- But if you're a pioneer, it must be really easy for you, right? I'd be super happy if you could get one for me.
        ALL_I_NEED_IS_PLEASE                                                          = 8130,  -- All I need is %. Please?
        YOU_VE_BROUGHT_ME_THE_GREAT                                                   = 8131,  -- You've brought me the %! Great!
        YOU_PIONEERS_ARE_GREAT_NOW_I_LL_ACE                                           = 8132,  -- You pioneers are great! Now I'll ace my project for sure!
        I_GO_TO_A_SCHOOL_ESTABLISHED_BY_THE                                           = 8133,  -- I go to a school established by the Order of Renaye and run by the minister of education. Because it's run by the city, it's free to everyone!
        THERE_ARE_MANY_POOR_FAMILIES_LIKE_MINE_SO                                     = 8134,  -- There are many poor families like mine, so I think it's great that we're able to study at such a wonderful place!
        WHEN_I_GROW_UP_AND_BECOME_A_PIONEER                                           = 8135,  -- When I grow up and become a pioneer, I'll be able to help my mother live a better life.
        I_CAN_T_OFFER_YOU_TOO_MUCH_BUT                                                = 8136,  -- I can't offer you too much, but maybe you'll find this useful? Either way, thank you so much for helping me!
        THIS_IS_AMCHUCHU_S_RESIDENCE_THE_LIBRARY_SENT                                 = 8137,  -- This is Amchuchu's residence. The library sent you? Give me a look at what they want.
        THERE_S_A_BIT_MORE_TO_ADD_ABOUT                                               = 8138,  -- There's a bit more to add about the Order of Orvail. Here. Tell them to use this instead.
        HOW_IS_THE_MUMMERS_COALITION_TREATING_YOU_WHAT                                = 8139,  -- How is the Mummers' Coalition treating you? What? You are here on behalf of the library?
        LET_ME_SEE_NO_I_DO_NOT_SEE                                                    = 8140,  -- Let me see...no, I do not see anything wrong here. Let them know everything is accurate and up-to-date.
        MISTRESS_SVENJA_IS_UNAVAILABLE_AT_THE_MOMENT_BUT                              = 8141,  -- Mistress Svenja is unavailable at the moment...but you say you're here to do some research for the library?
        HMM_NO_I_SEE_NO_PROBLEM_WITH_YOUR                                             = 8142,  -- Hmm... No, I see no problem with your records on the Order of Janniston. Carry on.
        YES_THIS_IS_THE_MANSE_OF_REGINALD_MAESTER                                     = 8143,  -- Yes, this is the manse of Reginald, maester of the Couriers' Coalition.
        YOUR_INFORMATION_ON_THE_ORDER_OF_SHNEDDICK_IS                                 = 8144,  -- Your information on the Order of Shneddick is accurate, at least to the best of my knowledge. Thank you for confirming. Once you're done with that task, stop by the coalition and lend them a hand, okay?
        WELCOME_YOU_RE_HERE_ON_BEHALF_OF_THE                                          = 8145,  -- Welcome. You're here on behalf of the library, yes?
        THEIR_RECORDS_OF_OUR_ORDER_APPEAR_TO_BE                                       = 8146,  -- Their records of our order appear to be complete. Thank you for coming to check.
