        MY_GUESS_IS_WE_LL_FIND_THAT_SERPENT                                           = 9145,  -- My guess is we'll find that serpent of the sky roosting there, shimmering scales and all. At least that's what the words of my father's poem say to me.
        IN_AN_EAGE_WHENCE_SCHADE_DENNEN_HIS_LAND                                      = 9146,  -- In an eage whence schade dennen his land, the ore of the swallow's witeword shalt be fulfilled.
        THE_WARANTS_OF_FOREST_SHALT_RAISE_THE_MERKE                                   = 9147,  -- The warants of forest shalt raise the merke blade high, and one of the whyte fether shalt florischen the swerdes sext.
        IF_WE_ARE_TO_BELIEVE_IN_THEM_THEN                                             = 9148,  -- If we are to believe in them, then the dragon that resides there is probably the key to quelling the strange plague afflicting our continent.
        FOR_THESE_REASONS_AND_MORE_WOULD_YOU_MIND                                     = 9149,  -- For these reasons and more, %, would you mind accompanying me to the top of Mount Kamihr?
        ACCOMPANY_HER_YES_OF_COURSE_NO_MY_ORE                                         = 9150,  -- Accompany her? Yes, of course. No, my ore collection calls.
        THANK_YOU_SO_MUCH                                                             = 9151,  -- Thank you so much!
        COME_TO_THINK_OF_IT_I_VE_NEVER                                                = 9152,  -- Come to think of it, I've never actually met a dragon face-to-face...err...snout. I can't help but feel afraid at just the thought of it.
        AT_LEAST_YOU_LL_BE_BY_MY_SIDE                                                 = 9153,  -- At least you'll be by my side, %. As an adventurer, you've probably bested whole broods of them.
        IF_THAT_S_THE_CASE_THEN_I_HAVE                                                = 9154,  -- If that's the case, then I have nothing to fear at all! How lucky I am to have met you.
        ENOUGH_TWITTERING_LIKE_A_SCHOOLGIRL_THOUGH_THIS_IS                            = 9155,  -- Enough twittering like a schoolgirl, though. This is no trivial matter. When you've properly steeled yourself for the journey, come meet me at Jorius Yett.
        HM_NO_I_NEVER_ONCE_THOUGHT_ABOUT_STOPPING                                     = 9156,  -- Hm? No, I never once thought about stopping Arciela.
        WHY_BECAUSE_DESPITE_HER_CLAIMS_OF_BEING_SCARED                                = 9157,  -- Why? Because, despite her claims of being scared, I'm confident that she's as tough as any dragon. Besides, she's ventured deep into the jungle countless times already, no?
        DON_T_GO_SPREADING_THIS_AROUND_BUT_I                                          = 9158,  -- Don't go spreading this around, but I might have some juicy tidbits for you to chew on.
        YOU_KNOW_HOW_YOU_SAID_YOU_HAD_NO                                              = 9159,  -- You know how you said you had no idea whether or not Arciela was carried off by some beast? Well, I might have overheard the answer.
        WORD_HAS_IT_THAT_SHE_WAS_INDEED_DRAGGED                                       = 9160,  -- Word has it that she was indeed dragged away in the bloodstained maw of some otherworldly abomination while resting outside the city gates! Does that get your knees a-knockin' or what?
        YOU_CAN_BE_SURE_THAT_ARCIELA_HAD_THE                                          = 9161,  -- You can be sure that Arciela had the worst of it, but even the Order of Weatherspoon-led search party traveled a rocky road straight off the cliff of humiliation.
        THEY_NOT_ONLY_FAILED_TO_FIND_ANY_CLUES                                        = 9162,  -- They not only failed to find any clues as to her whereabouts by themselves, but were ambushed by hordes of creatures, the likes of which were heretofore undocumented. Some members even returned with grave wounds...supposedly inflicted by a tiger of monumental stature.
        LUCKILY_SOME_CAPABLE_PIONEERS_STUMBLED_UPON_THEM_AND                          = 9163,  -- Luckily, some capable pioneers stumbled upon them and were able to use their superior tracking skills to lead the exorcists to our princess. A close call, for certain.
        AND_WHAT_OF_ARCIELA_I_HEAR_YOU_THINKING                                       = 9164,  -- And what of Arciela, I hear you thinking.
        THE_POWERS_THAT_BE_WITHIN_THE_TWELVE_ORDERS                                   = 9165,  -- The powers that be within the Twelve Orders forcefully persuaded the Order of Adoulin to forbid her from entering the jungle, on account of the dangers present there.
        I_UNDERSTAND_THEIR_CAUSE_FOR_CONCERN_SEEING_AS                                = 9166,  -- I understand their cause for concern, seeing as how Arciela's to be the next in line to lead the nation, should her brother's health continue to fail.
        ANYTHING_TO_SAY_LONG_LIVE_YGNAS_WHAT_HAPPENED                                 = 9167,  -- Anything to say? Long live Ygnas! What happened after that?
        YOU_SURE_YOUR_BRAIN_ISN_T_IN_AN                                               = 9168,  -- ...You sure your brain isn't in an otherworldly skirmish right now?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_THINK_HAPPENED                                                    = 9169,  -- What do you think happened?
        SHE_S_NOT_ONE_TO_JUST_LIE_THERE                                               = 9170,  -- She's not one to just lie there after falling off her horse. She got back up and registered herself as a pioneer, that's what!
        I_BELIEVE_HER_EXACT_WORDS_WERE_OUR_SOVEREIGN                                  = 9171,  -- I believe her exact words were, Our sovereign nation is no monarchy, nor is anyone from our order guaranteed a position of leadership. As long as my brother remains the chancellor, I am just another citizen of this fine city.
        FURTHERMORE_AS_ANY_CITIZEN_MAY_APPLY_TO_BECOME                                = 9172,  -- Furthermore, as any citizen may apply to become a pioneer, I choose to exercise that right. I assume none of you take issue with the legislation you first enacted, do you?
        I_JUST_ABOUT_SPIT_THE_FRONTIER_SODA_I                                         = 9173,  -- I just about spit the frontier soda I was drinking all over Lhe when I heard about it! To think that Arciela already wants to head back into the jungle despite almost being devoured.
        OR_IS_IT_EXACTLY_BECAUSE_OF_THAT_EXPERIENCE                                   = 9174,  -- ...Or is it exactly because of that experience that she decided to get official permission this time?
        ALTHOUGH_I_GUESS_THE_MAESTERS_AND_MINISTERS_WOULD                             = 9175,  -- Although, I guess the maesters and ministers would rather have her traipsing about the forest under the auspices of the Pioneers' Coalition than sneaking off in the dead of night.
        NONE_OF_THIS_REALLY_ANSWERS_THE_QUESTION_OF                                   = 9176,  -- None of this really answers the question of what that monster wanted from her, but maybe this is a perfect case of all's well that ends well.
        ANYWAY_THE_BOTTOM_LINE_IS_THAT_NO_ONE                                         = 9177,  -- Anyway, the bottom line is that no one can stop Arciela now.
        IT_S_NOT_LIKE_SHE_LL_BE_COMPLETELY                                            = 9178,  -- It's not like she'll be completely on her own, either. Her order will be informed each and every time she passes through Jorius Yett, and they're bound to employ a bodyguard for her when you're off slicing your way through the jungle.
        NOW_WHEN_YOU_ESCORT_THE_PRINCESS_YOU_LL                                       = 9179,  -- Now when you escort the princess, you'll not only have her opinion of you on your mind, but the eyes of every member of every Adoulinian order on your back!
        DOES_THAT_GET_YOUR_BLOOD_PUMPING_OR_WHAT                                      = 9180,  -- Does that get your blood pumping or what? Hahaha.
        IN_ALL_SERIOUSNESS_THOUGH_I_BELIEVE_IN_YOU                                    = 9181,  -- In all seriousness, though, I believe in you. The fate of our princess is in your hands, %!
        I_VE_NEVER_SEEN_A_MORE_DETERMINED_FACE                                        = 9182,  -- I've never seen a more determined face than yours is right now, %. Good to know you're ready.
        WELL_THEN_SHALL_WE_GET_GOING_FOR_MOUNT                                        = 9183,  -- Well then, shall we get going for Mount Kamihr?
        AH_YES_THAT_CERTAINLY_IS_A_TASK                                               = 9184,  -- Ah, yes, that certainly is...a task.
        WELL_IF_YOU_FINISH_WITH_THAT_AND_WOULD                                        = 9185,  -- Well, if you finish with that and would condescend to help uncover a continent's history, then I'll be waiting for you.
        COME_ON_EVEN_I_WOULDN_T_USE_THAT                                              = 9186,  -- (Come on, %, even I wouldn't use that poor of an excuse.)
        REGARDLESS_HOW_CAN_YOU_REFUSE_HER_POLITE_REQUEST                              = 9187,  -- (Regardless, how can you refuse her polite request when you see how serious she is? Just look at those eyes!)
        WHY_RE_YOU_HERE_ALL_BY_YOUR_LONESOME                                          = 9188,  -- Why're you here all by your lonesome and not out escorting the princess!? Didn't my talk scare you straight at all?
        AN_UNTAINTED_SECTION_OF_THE_FOREST_HMM_YOU                                    = 9189,  -- An untainted section of the forest, hmm? You mean like a new ergon locus?
        HMM_THIS_MIGHT_BE_A_BIT_OF_A                                                  = 9190,  -- Hmm...this might be a bit of a long shot, but... One of your pioneer buddies came by the other day, saying that he saw a wooded area deep within Kamihr Drifts.
        I_VE_NEVER_BEEN_OUT_THERE_MYSELF_BUT                                          = 9191,  -- I've never been out there myself, but it doesn't make any sense. There's no business for a forest to be in that desolate wasteland.
        ON_THE_OTHER_HAND_ULBUKA_IS_A_LAND                                            = 9192,  -- On the other hand, Ulbuka is a land of mysteries. Who can really tell? Yorcia and Hennetiel are forests, and the soil there reeks of poison.
        ON_THE_THIRD_HAND_FROSTBITE_DOES_STRANGE_THINGS                               = 9193,  -- On the third hand, frostbite does strange things to a man's faculties.
        SORRY_I_PROBABLY_LEFT_YOU_MORE_CONFUSED_THAN                                  = 9194,  -- Sorry, %. I probably left you more confused than when you came in.
