        GOT_IT_THEN_DIG_YOUR_SPURS_IN_AND                                             = 9788,  -- Got it? Then dig your spurs in and get a move on! Otherwise there'll be a showdown at the Brenton Corral between the powers that be and me, and the odds aren't in my favor.
        YOU_STILL_BUSY_CORRALLIN_VICIOUS_BEASTS_AND_SURVEYIN                          = 9789,  -- You still busy corrallin' vicious beasts and surveyin' the land?
        WELL_KEEP_UP_THE_GOOD_WORK_PARDNER                                            = 9790,  -- Well, keep up the good work, pardner.
        DON_T_THINK_THAT_SINCE_YOU_VE_DONE                                            = 9791,  -- Don't think that since you've done a few good deeds here and there that you can saddle up on your high horse, though. Give your all to diff'rent coalitions and they'll give you back just as much in return.
        I_WELCOME_YOU_WITH_OPEN_ARMS_TO_THE                                           = 9792,  -- I welcome you with open arms to the Pioneers' Coalition!
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_TO_REGISTER_AS_A_PIONEER                                    = 9793,  -- Should you desire to register as a pioneer, my arms would open even wider. Or, we could have all our members join hands and hug you all at once, since we'd be like a family! Either way, just head to the desk in back to get started on the greatest adventure of your life!
        BE_YOU_ANOTHER_OF_THEM_WOULD_BE_PIONEERS                                      = 9794,  -- Be you another of them would-be pioneers, filled with aspirations and promise? Then saunter on over to the back, there. We'll get you all set up.
        FEELING_DOWN_WELL_SAVE_THE_WATERWORKS_FOR_THE                                 = 9795,  -- Feeling down? Well save the waterworks for the Waterways, as I always say! Wipe away the tears, here comes the cheer: If we all work together, we can change the continent for the better! Hmmm...still needs some work, I guess.
        IF_YOU_EVER_HAPPEN_TO_CROSS_PATHS_WITH                                        = 9796,  -- If you ever happen to cross paths with the leader of our coalition, don't speak unless you're spoken to. The amount of work she piles on people is enough to turn the sunniest summer afternoon into the dreariest of winter nights.
        PUMP_THOSE_TRUSTY_LEGS_OF_YOURS_ON_OVER                                       = 9797,  -- Pump those trusty legs of yours on over to the counter there if you'd like to register as a pioneer.
        A_WORD_OF_ADVICE_THOUGH_IF_I_MAY                                              = 9798,  -- A word of advice, though, if I may. Should you have the misfortune to bump into our maester, you best be at your most humble lest you find yourself buried under a mountain of work.
        HOW_S_THE_OLD_PIONEERING_BEEN_GOING                                           = 9799,  -- How's the old pioneering been going?
        NOW_THAT_THE_PIONEERS_COALITION_HAS_GOTTEN_OFF                                = 9800,  -- Now that the Pioneers' Coalition has gotten off the ground a bit, they're handing out items to help during reives and the like.
        WE_LL_BE_PRACTICALLY_THROWING_PROVISIONS_AT_PIONEERS                          = 9801,  -- We'll be practically throwing provisions at pioneers left and right when the time comes for a reive, so don't forget this weathered old face of mine, okay?
        ONE_DAY_WE_SHALL_FEEL_THE_CHAOS_RUSHING                                       = 9802,  -- One day, we shall feel The chaos rushing 'round us Put into order.
        LO_GEOMANCY_YOU_RE_THE_EBB_AND_FLOW                                           = 9803,  -- Lo, Geomancy! You're the ebb and flow of land We long to harness.
        THANKS_TO_ALL_THE_MIDDLE_LANDERS_THIS_TOWN                                    = 9804,  -- Thanks to all the Middle Landers, this town's bristling with more people than hairs on a Mithra!
        GETS_ME_TO_THINKING_I_SHOULD_OPEN_UP                                          = 9805,  -- Gets me to thinking I should open up my own shop before this boom goes bust. Say, you want in on the ground floor? I think I'll need about three million to start...
        WHAT_DOES_THE_COURIERS_COALITION_DO_LIKE_THE                                  = 9806,  -- What does the Couriers' Coalition do? Like the name implies, we transport supplies.
        THAT_S_WHY_WE_NEED_BETTER_ROADS_HOW                                           = 9807,  -- That's why we need better roads. How can we carry stuff efficiently if we have to worry about rocks and potholes?
        NO_OFFENSE_MEANT_TO_YOU_THE_MORE_YOU                                          = 9808,  -- No offense meant to you. The more you pioneers explore, the easier it is for us to do our jobs, so keep up the good work!
        OHO_A_PASSING_ADVENTURER_ARE_WE_WELL_AS                                       = 9809,  -- ...Oho, a passing adventurer, are we? Well, as you can see, all I do is stand outside this manse all day, so how about indulging me in a talk about Adoulinian history?
        THE_CITY_IS_GOVERNED_BY_REPRESENTATIVES_FROM_THE                              = 9810,  -- The city is governed by representatives from the Twelve Orders, the original leaders of which were knights who valiantly served the founder king.
        MY_ESTEEMED_EMPLOYER_SVENJA_THE_MINISTER_OF_PUBLIC                            = 9811,  -- My esteemed employer, Svenja--the minister of public affairs--hails from the Order of Janniston. Her title may sound ambiguous, but it just means that she must try her utmost to make Adoulin a habitable place.
        THE_LEADERS_OF_THE_SIX_COALITIONS_ARE_ALL                                     = 9812,  -- The leaders of the six coalitions are all termed maesters. I guess it's logical enough, seeing as how they are masters of their trade, but master just doesn't have the same ring to it.
        ANYWAY_THE_OTHER_HALF_OF_ADOULIN_S_COUNCIL                                    = 9813,  -- Anyway, the other half of Adoulin's council seats are filled by the six ministers, for a total of twelve representatives, all belonging to one of the Twelve Orders. ...Yeah, that last name isn't quite so impressive.
        THANKS_FOR_LISTENING_TO_ME_NOT_ENOUGH_PEOPLE                                  = 9814,  -- Thanks for listening to me. Not enough people stop and talk to each other these days. In return for your kindness, why don't I tell you a little secret about one of the meisters?
        RUMOR_HAS_IT_THAT_MAESTER_REGINALD_OF_THE                                     = 9815,  -- Rumor has it that Maester Reginald of the Couriers' Coalition is a spy sent from the Middle Lands so that Jeuno can annex Ulbuka and reap its abundant harvests! That's why he's so by-the-book...to cover his tracks!
        HOW_ABOUT_INDULGING_IN_SOME_REGIONAL_DELICACIES_WHILE                         = 9816,  -- How about indulging in some regional delicacies while taking a load off those tired feet of yours?
        WANT_A_WAY_TO_BEAT_THE_HEAT_TRY                                               = 9817,  -- Want a way to beat the heat? Try some of the tasty beverages we have on hand.
        WHAT_CAN_THE_COURIERS_COALITION_DO_FOR_YOU                                    = 9818,  -- What can the Couriers' Coalition do for you? Why, only ensure the integrity of every shipment from origin to destination!
        SPEAKING_OF_DESTINATIONS_I_D_WAGER_THAT_YOURS                                 = 9819,  -- Speaking of destinations, I'd wager that yours is the Pioneers' Coalition down the road that leads to the western gate.
        WHAT_YOU_HAVEN_T_REGISTERED_AS_A_PIONEER                                      = 9820,  -- What!? You haven't registered as a pioneer yet!?
        DON_T_GIVE_ME_THAT_I_M_UNDECIDED                                              = 9821,  -- Don't give me that I'm undecided crap! Go talk to Brenton in the Pioneers' Coalition before I carry you over there myself!
        YOU_TAKE_ANY_OFFERS_FROM_THE_COURIERS_COALITION                               = 9822,  -- You take any offers from the Couriers' Coalition yet? It's never too late to start.
        IF_YOU_ALREADY_HAVE_THEN_YOU_MIGHT_AS                                         = 9823,  -- If you already have, then you might as well take a waypoint! No sense in throwing your back out, right?
        ALTHOUGH_YOU_CAN_T_WARP_TO_ANY_FRONTIER                                       = 9824,  -- Although...you can't warp to any frontier stations unless you've been to them before, so maybe it doesn't matter for you yet.
        MOVE_IT_OUT_OF_THE_WAY_I_M                                                    = 9825,  -- Move it! Out of the way! I'm on my way to breaking my personal speed record for carrying important stuff!
        NOOO_I_JUST_REALIZED_I_HAVE_TO_GO                                             = 9826,  -- Nooo! I just realized I have to go west from the city and pass through the Ceizak Battlegrounds!
        I_HAVE_TO_DEAL_WITH_ALL_THOSE_DISGUSTING                                      = 9827,  -- I have to deal with all those disgusting vermin as soon as I leave the city!? I'll have to take it slow this time. Well, there goes my bet.
        UNDER_THE_BRIDGE_AND_TO_THE_NORTH_TOWARD                                      = 9828,  -- Under the bridge and to the north, toward Adoulin Waterfront you'll go. Keep walking that way, and then...you'll find an airship dock, oh yay!t
        BUT_ONCE_YOU_TAKE_TO_THE_SKIES_YOU                                            = 9829,  -- But once you take to the skies, you'll likely die, So we've barred most passengers, you know.t
        PLEASE_USE_BOATS_TO_TAKE_YOU_AWAY_ONES                                        = 9830,  -- Please use boats to take you away--ones that dock at the Waterfront all day. There'll be workers there running faster than the west winds blow.t
        SIR_MADAME_KNOW_YOU_OF_THE_COURIERS_COALITION                                 = 9831,  -- Sir/Madame], know you of the Couriers' Coalition? We supervise the domestic transport and inspection of all provisions in a very thorough manner, if I do say so myself.
        I_MUST_ADMIT_HOWEVER_THAT_THE_IMPECCABLE_WORK                                 = 9832,  -- I must admit, however, that the impeccable work ethic exhibited by most of our members stems not from passion, but from fear of retribution from the Order of Woltaris.
        I_M_TRANSPORTING_STUFF_FOR_THE_COURIERS_COALITION                             = 9833,  -- I'm transporting stuff for the Couriers' Coalition. What's it look like? Gotta make sure these packages from the waterfront get to whom they should.
        LISTEN_TO_THIS_THERE_S_A_PASSAGEWAY_THAT                                      = 9834,  -- Listen to this. There's a passageway that leads to the Rala Waterways, right?
        LATELY_PEOPLE_HAVE_BEEN_HEARING_SOME_DECIDEDLY_GROTESQUE                      = 9835,  -- Lately, people have been hearing some decidedly grotesque wails and grunts coming from inside.
        THE_BEASTS_DOWN_THERE_ARE_SUPPOSEDLY_SEALED_OFF                               = 9836,  -- The beasts down there are supposedly sealed off with magic, and the Peacekeepers' Coalition has a post down there, so there shouldn't be anything to worry about...I hope.
        MOST_OF_THE_PEOPLE_AROUND_HERE_WORK_FOR                                       = 9837,  -- Most of the people around here work for the Couriers' Coalition, and I'm no exception.
        WE_IMPORT_AND_EXPORT_GOODS_MAKE_INTERCONTINENTAL_DELIVERIES                   = 9838,  -- We import and export goods, make intercontinental deliveries, and provide supplies to pioneer facilities. I'm not a man of many words, so I'll leave it at that.
        THIS_IS_INDEED_THE_AIRSHIP_DOCKS_I_M                                          = 9839,  -- This is indeed the airship docks. I'm sorry if you were hoping to use its services, but we are under strict orders not to allow any civilians on board.
        MY_SINCEREST_APOLOGIES_BUT_OUR_MECHANICS_ARE_CURRENTLY                        = 9840,  -- My sincerest apologies, but our mechanics are currently investigating the source of a problem with our ship's crystal propulsion system.
        THE_COURIERS_COALITION_ISN_T_SIMPLY_AN_ASSEMBLY                               = 9841,  -- The Couriers' Coalition isn't simply an assembly of grunts who carry heavy things long distances. We are the blood that flows swiftly and efficiently through Ulbuka's body, providing it much-needed nutrition.
        SOUNDS_PROFOUND_RIGHT_THAT_S_BECAUSE_THEY_RE                                  = 9842,  -- Sounds profound, right? That's because they're words from none other than our leader, Reginald. He also has this one: Ulbuka lives and dies by the effort the Couriers' Coalition puts forth.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_WANT_TO_HELP_HOW                                              = 9843,  -- What's that? You want to help? How kind of you!
        FOLLOW_ME_THEN_IT_LL_TAKE_A_WHILE                                             = 9844,  -- Follow me, then! It'll take a while, though. The spot I'm in charge of is so far away that I think my boss must have it in for me.
        THERE_S_A_GOOD_REASON_VELKK_ARE_KNOWN                                         = 9845,  -- There's a good reason Velkk are known as the Eventide Savages. They've been trying to raze our sacred city for as long as I remember!
        I_DON_T_CARE_WHAT_THAT_OLD_TOME                                               = 9846,  -- I don't care what that old tome in the library says! This is our city now, and the Velkk can't have it back!
        EVERY_PROVISION_THAT_BENEFITS_ADOULIN_OR_THE_PIONEERING                       = 9847,  -- Every provision that benefits Adoulin or the pioneering effort passes through this warehouse at some point.
        TOO_BAD_THESE_SHIPS_WAIT_FOR_NO_GALKA                                         = 9848,  -- Too bad these ships wait for no Galka. I go home every night with blisters on my hands. Sometimes even trails of dried tears on my cheeks.
        JORIN_S_THE_NAME_AND_FISHIN_S_MY                                              = 9849,  -- Jorin's the name and fishin's my game, sonny boy/little missy]. That's why I'm so int'rested in them pioneers colonizin' Foret de Hennetiel. Hopefully I'll be able to catch me some whoppers when they's done.
        I_D_GO_BY_MYSELF_NOW_BUT_WHATEVER                                             = 9850,  -- I'd go by myself now, but whatever I fish up be likely doused in Zoldeff River poisons. I remember the last time my wife ate one o' them. She done repainted our interior with what she threw up!
        WE_VE_GOT_A_DOOZY_OF_A_MAGIC                                                  = 9851,  -- We've got a doozy of a magic scroll selection, tailored especially to your pioneering needs!
        A_PIONEER_ARE_YA_IF_THAT_S_THE                                                = 9852,  -- ...A pioneer, are ya? If that's the case, maybe we've finally found a client for our geomantic plates.
        WHY_HELLO_THERE_IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR                                         = 9853,  -- Why, hello there! If you're looking for geomantic plates, look no further! I don't like to brag, but I'd say our selection is a bit more...sophisticated than what they offer next door.
        WELCOME_WELCOME_GOING_OUT_INTO_THE_EYE_OF                                     = 9854,  -- Welcome, welcome! Going out into the eye of the jungle's storm? Then the last thing you want is your stomach rumbling during an important battle!
        YOU_EVER_HEAR_ABOUT_RRRUNE_FENCERS                                            = 9855,  -- You ever hear about rrrune fencers?
        THEY_RE_ACCOMPLISHED_SWORRRDSMEN_WHO_MAKE_USE_OF                              = 9856,  -- They're accomplished sworrrdsmen who make use of runes to snuff out their enemies and empower their friends. Their techniques may have been passed down through the Order of Orvail for generrrations, but even I could use them if I stopped catting around for once.
        HAVE_YOU_TRIED_ANY_OF_THE_DELECTABLE_CUISINE                                  = 9857,  -- Have you tried any of the delectable cuisine Adoulin has to offer?
        WITH_THE_SEA_MERE_YALMS_AWAY_YOU_LL                                           = 9858,  -- With the sea mere yalms away, you'll never want for the freshest of fish and other aquatic life to tantalize your palate!
        WOULD_YOU_CARE_FOR_SOME_OF_MY_WARES                                           = 9859,  -- Would you care for some of my wares? If you do not, I cannot fault you, but please keep in mind that my revolutionary research into a new Ulbukan toxin antidote will have to be put on hold unless I can accrue the necessary funds.
        GOOD_DAY_GOOD_SIR_FAIR_MAIDEN_YOU_RE                                          = 9860,  -- Good day, good sir/fair maiden]! You're certainly not in the Middle Lands anymore, but would you care for some products from your homeland in addition to some more traditional fare?
        JUST_A_SHORT_JAUNTARU_OVER_BIG_BRIDGE_WILL                                    = 9861,  -- Just a short jauntaru over Big Bridge will take you into Eastern Adoulin!
        COINCIDENTARULY_THAT_S_ALSO_WHERE_THE_PEACEKEEPERS_COALITION                  = 9862,  -- Coincidentaruly, that's also where the Peacekeepers' Coalition is stationed. We watch over all the citizen-witizens of the city!
        WE_WATCH_FROM_WITHIN_GUARD_TOWERS_FROM_UPON                                   = 9863,  -- We watch from within guard towers, from upon the city walls, from everywhere! Sometimes our hardened gaze even awakens certain dormantaru feelings with people, which end up coming back to bite us.
        YOU_WOULD_BE_SORELY_MISINFORMED_WERE_YOU_TO                                   = 9864,  -- You would be sorely misinformed were you to believe that everyone in Adoulin supports the colonization effort.
        A_FAMOUS_EXAMPLE_WOULD_BE_THE_LEADER_OF                                       = 9865,  -- A famous example would be the leader of the Peacekeepers' Coalition, Gratzigg. I personally think that his views on the topic are outdated and overly conservative, but to each his own.
        WE_SHAN_T_BE_ABLE_TO_COLONIZE_ULBUKA                                          = 9866,  -- We shan't be able to colonize Ulbuka if pioneers are overly tired, no?
        WE_AT_THE_MUMMERS_COALITION_WORK_AS_HARD                                      = 9867,  -- We at the Mummers' Coalition work as hard as possible to ensure those providing a brighter future for the continent never lose their ambition. We endeavor to keep morale high by providing festive functions and other joyous events year-round.
        SPEAKING_OF_OUR_FINE_INSTITUTION_THIS_REGAL_ESTATE                            = 9868,  -- Speaking of our fine institution, this regal estate belongs to Flaviria, the esteemed leader of our coalition. Without her, living in this city would be a much less pleasurable experience.
        THIS_IS_ADOULIN_S_MANUFACTURING_DISTRICT_THERE_ARE                            = 9869,  -- This is Adoulin's manufacturing district. There are lots of workshops here.
        AMCHUCHU_THE_MAESTER_OF_THE_INVENTORS_COALITION_KEEPS                         = 9870,  -- Amchuchu, the maester of the Inventors' Coalition, keeps everything running smoothly.
        SOMETIMES_YOU_SEE_HER_JOKING_WITH_IKHI_ASKAMOT                                = 9871,  -- Sometimes you see her joking with Ikhi Askamot. That's her friend from the Order of Renaye. They look cute together.
        IF_YOU_CAME_HERE_SEEKING_THE_BRIGHTARUEST_MINDS                               = 9872,  -- If you came here seeking the brightaruest minds in all of Adoulin, then you're in luck! Welcome to the Inventors' Coalition.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_BE_INTARUSTED_IN_MAKING                                      = 9873,  -- If you happen to be intarusted in making your creations come to life, make sure to remember our name. You might want to make a note of mine, too, if you want to set up a meeting of the minds.
        GOODNESS_GRACIOUS_WACIOUS_YOU_HAVEN_T_REGISTERED_AS                           = 9874,  -- Goodness gracious-wacious! You haven't registered as a pioneer yet? Then pay a visitaru to the Pioneers' Coalition along the main thoroughfare to the west.
        FEAST_YOUR_EYES_UPON_ONE_OF_THE_BEST                                          = 9875,  -- Feast your eyes upon one of the best waypoints in all of Adoulin! Why's it one of the best? Because it's an Inventors' Coalition waypoint, that's why!
        IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_AN_OUTSIDER_LIKE_YOU_TO                                      = 9876,  -- ...It would behoove an outsider like you to register as a pioneer before entering our premises, but I will not force you to leave. Take a look around our facilities, but do not interfere with anyone's work.
        IT_IS_IMPERATIVE_THAT_YOU_BE_ABLE_TO                                          = 9877,  -- It is imperative that you be able to properly use the tools with which we, the Inventors' Coalition, supply you. Otherwise, the colonization effort is doomed to fail.
        HI_THERE_PIONEER_WE_WOULDN_T_WANT_YOU                                         = 9878,  -- Hi there, pioneer! We wouldn't want you going out to the scary jungle on an empty stomach. Stock up on some of our delicious bread for the journey!
        WOULD_YOU_CARE_FOR_SOME_FRESH_VEGETABLES_DIRECT                               = 9879,  -- Would you care for some fresh vegetables direct from the Rala Waterways? They're some of our most popular items!
        HIDEY_HO_MAKE_SURE_NOT_TO_FORGETARU_ANYTHING                                  = 9880,  -- Hidey ho! Make sure not to forgetaru anything before heading out into the great unknown!
        MY_MOTHER_SAYS_THAT_PIONEERS_MUST_HAVE_BRAINS                                 = 9881,  -- My mother says that pioneers must have brains as well as brawn.
        I_WISH_TO_STUDY_HARD_AND_BECOME_A                                             = 9882,  -- I wish to study hard and become a great pioneer soon! Then maybe I can let her take a break from working so often.
        I_M_GOING_TO_TRAIN_HARD_AND_BE                                                = 9883,  -- I'm going to train hard and be a pioneer. I'll colonize all of Ulbuka by myself!
        THEN_I_LL_BRING_BACK_THE_NEW_MATERIALS                                        = 9884,  -- Then I'll bring back the new materials I find. I'll make amazing new inventions with them. No one will call me Milquetoast Merleg ever again!
        THE_WATERCRAFT_THAT_DOCK_HERE_TRANSPORT_PIONEERS_AND                          = 9885,  -- The watercraft that dock here transport pioneers and laymen alike to their private island plots replete with a cornucopia of facilities.
        ABOUT_WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_KNOW_NOTHING                                     = 9886,  -- About what would you like to know? Nothing. Send me to my Mog Garden! Visiting others' Mog Gardens. Rent-a-Rooms. Mog Gardens. Expanding my Mog Garden.
        THERE_SHALL_BE_NO_STOWING_AWAY_WHILE_I                                        = 9887,  -- There shall be no stowing away while I'm on watch! Only registered pioneers are allowed aboard this vessel, you imposter!
        IF_I_WERE_TO_DESCRIBE_WHAT_A_RENT                                             = 9888,  -- If I were to describe what a Rent-a-Room means to pioneers in one word, it would be convenience.
        THEY_ARE_POSITIONED_UPON_DESERTED_ISLANDS_THAT_CAME                           = 9889,  -- They are positioned upon deserted islands that came under Adoulin's jurisdiction once the alliance was formed and the old regime abandoned. As for amenities, the Rent-a-Rooms mirror those of similar facilities across Vana'diel.
        WE_ALSO_PLAN_TO_OFFER_PIONEERS_ACCESS_TO                                      = 9890,  -- We also plan to offer pioneers access to their own personal Mog Garden in the future.
        WE_ARE_STILL_IN_THE_PROCESS_OF_APPLYING                                       = 9891,  -- We are still in the process of applying the finishing touches to these establishments, so I kindly entreat you to bear with us until their completion.
        MOG_GARDENS_ARE_SPECIAL_AREAS_LOCATED_ON_THE                                  = 9892,  -- Mog Gardens are special areas located on the islands dotting the Adoulin Archipelago which have a variety of facilities suited for all your gathering needs.
        ABSOLUTELY_NO_FEE_IS_REQUIRED_TO_TAKE_ADVANTAGE                               = 9893,  -- Absolutely no fee is required to take advantage of this service.
        WE_HOPE_THAT_YOU_UTILIZE_YOUR_MOG_GARDEN                                      = 9894,  -- We hope that you utilize your Mog Garden to the fullest.
        NOW_THAT_THE_PIONEERS_COALITION_HAS_UNDERGONE_A                               = 9895,  -- Now that the Pioneers' Coalition has undergone a certain degree of edification, you are able to expand your Mog Garden!
        WHAT_MAKES_THIS_NEWS_EVEN_MORE_JOYOUS_IS                                      = 9896,  -- What makes this news even more joyous is that should the Pioneers' Coalition fall on hard times and need to consolidate its services, your Mog Garden will still retain its newfound glory.
        YOU_MAY_VISIT_THE_MOG_GARDENS_OF_THE                                          = 9897,  -- You may visit the Mog Gardens of the following party members. Is there anyone's in particular you would care to visit?
        VISIT_WHOSE_MOG_GARDEN_NO_ONE_S_S                                             = 9898,  -- Visit whose Mog Garden? No one's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's. 's.
        YOUR_WISH_IS_MY_COMMAND_THIS_WAY_PLEASE                                       = 9899,  -- Your wish is my command. This way, please.
        I_REGRET_TO_INFORM_YOU_THAT_NONE_OF                                           = 9900,  -- I regret to inform you that none of your party members are currently allowing people to patron their Mog Gardens.
        YOU_ARE_CURRENTLY_UNABLE_TO_VISIT_THAT_PERSON                                 = 9901,  -- You are currently unable to visit that person's Mog Garden.
        I_CAN_T_THANK_YOU_PIONEERS_ENOUGH_FOR                                         = 9902,  -- I can't thank you pioneers enough for coming to this continent. I've never seen Adoulin so lively in all my years of trading.
        I_MIGHT_HAVE_TO_INVEST_IN_A_PAIR                                              = 9903,  -- I might have to invest in a pair of sea legs soon, what with all the ships going back and forth between here and the Middle Lands. Hopefully these mercantile connections will bridge the cultural divisions between our two homes as well.
        OH_DEARY_WEARY_JUST_LOOK_AT_THOSE_TEETERING                                   = 9904,  -- Oh deary-weary, just look at those teetering-weetering legs of yours.
        I_KNOW_HOW_TO_RID_THEM_OF_THEIR                                               = 9905,  -- I know how to rid them of their strain! A tarurrific huggy-wug!
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MUMMERS_COALITION_WHERE_THE_PLEASURE                           = 9906,  -- Welcome to the Mummers' Coalition, where the pleasure and prrrosperity of Adoulin's people is our number one goal.
        SNIFF_AHA_I_CAN_SMELL_THE_ADVENTURER_ON                                       = 9907,  -- <Sniff>... Aha! I can smell the adventurer on you from a malm away. Then you should rrregister as a pioneer while you're here.
        HIGHTAIL_IT_OVER_TO_THE_PIONEERS_COALITION_JUST                               = 9908,  -- Hightail it over to the Pioneers' Coalition just down the rrroad and speak with Brenton. He'll get you all grrroomed and ready to help colonize the continent!
        IF_YOU_RE_A_FUN_LOVING_LORD_LADY                                              = 9909,  -- If you're a fun-loving lord/lady] looking for a good time, I'd be more than willing to show you to the Mummers' Coalition.t
        MY_OH_MY_YOU_RE_NOT_A_PIONEER                                                 = 9910,  -- My, oh my... You're not a pioneer? Then make haste to the Pioneers' Coalition so we can...enliven you as soon as possible!
        ALTANA_S_BLESSED_LIGHT_THAT_RUGGED_FACE_AND                                   = 9911,  -- Altana's blessed light! That rugged face and those rippling muscles of yours are making me faint of breath! It was almost enough to make me overlook the hint of fatigue in those enchanting eyes.
        WHAT_OUR_COALITION_S_MAESTER_WHY_WOULD_YOU                                    = 9912,  -- What? Our coalition's maester? Why would you want to know about that haggard old biddy!?
        THERE_S_NOTHING_ATTRACTIVE_ABOUT_HER_UNLESS_STINGINESS                        = 9913,  -- There's nothing attractive about her...unless stinginess flips your switch. Personally, I think I'm much more fabulous than her. Tee hee!
        OH_MY_GODDESS_LOOK_AT_THAT_EQUIPMENT_ENSEMBLE                                 = 9914,  -- Oh. My. Goddess. Look at that equipment ensemble! It looks fabulous on you...but I still think I'd wear it better.
        UGH_NOT_OUR_MAESTER_THE_MERE_MENTION_OF                                       = 9915,  -- Ugh, not our maester. The mere mention of her makes my hair stand on end!
        ALL_SHE_EVER_THINKS_ABOUT_IS_HOW_MUCH                                         = 9916,  -- All she ever thinks about is how much more bayld she can fit in those loose pockets of hers!
