        RESETTING_REWARDS_WILL_INCREASE_THE_NUMBER_OF_DEEDS                           = 11455,  -- Resetting rewards will increase the number of deeds required but will let you reobtain items you have previously received.
        YOU_ARE_ABLE_TO_RESET_YOUR_REWARDS_FOR                                        = 11456,  -- You are able to reset your rewards for # deed[/s].
        RESET_REWARDS_YES_RESET_NO                                                    = 11457,  -- Reset rewards? Yes. (Reset ##) No.
        YOU_HAVE_NOT_YET_RECEIVED_SOME_REWARDS_RESETTING                              = 11458,  -- You have not yet received some rewards. Resetting means that you will be unable to obtain them. Are you sure?
        REALLY_RESET_REWARDS_YES_RESET_NO                                             = 11459,  -- Really reset rewards? Yes. (Reset ##) No.
        REWARDS_HAVE_BEEN_RESET                                                       = 11460,  -- Rewards have been reset.
        I_PROMISE_THE_WORLD_WILL_UNFOLD_BEFORE_YOU                                    = 11461,  -- I promise the world will unfold before you if you set an Objective under the Records of Eminence section of the Quests menu.
        HMHMHM_WHATEVER_COULD_YOU_WANT_WITH_ME_THE                                    = 11462,  -- Hmhmhm? Whatever could you want with me, the one-and-only Love and Peace Coalition maester?
        ANYTHING_TO_SAY_THAT_TITLE_SOUNDS_FAKE_YOU                                    = 11463,  -- Anything to say? That title sounds fake. You creep me out. Nothing. Just walk away.
        WHAT_A_CRUEL_CRUEL_WORLD_WE_LIVE_IN                                           = 11464,  -- What a cruel, cruel world we live in. The people cry out for love with their hearts, but cannot bear to do it with their lips! They long for peace, but only seem to find it in solitude!
        THERE_S_NOTHING_SCARY_ABOUT_STANDING_IN_THE                                   = 11465,  -- There's nothing scary about standing in the center of Western Adoulin and professing my love for humanity. I am simply following the orders of divine provenance!
        IS_YOUR_LOVE_LARGER_THAN_THE_LARGEST_KINGDOM                                  = 11466,  -- Is your love larger than the largest kingdom and softer than a sough?
        WHAT_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_VE_NEVER                                               = 11467,  -- What? Don't tell me you've never heard of a one-man coalition.
        WAIT_A_SECOND_YOU_RE_ONE_OF_THOSE                                             = 11468,  -- Wait a second...you're one of those adventurers from the Middle Lands.
        OH_BOY_HAVE_I_GOT_SOMETHING_FOR_YOU                                           = 11469,  -- Oh boy, have I got something for you... You've already accomplished your first Records of Eminence objective just by calling out to me through the depths of loneliness!
        I_BEG_YOU_NOT_TO_STOP_HERE_NO                                                 = 11470,  -- I beg you not to stop here. No matter how difficult it may seem, do not stray from the path of self-improvement.
        IF_YOU_WON_T_DO_IT_FOR_YOURSELF                                               = 11471,  -- If you won't do it for yourself, then do it for all the spoils you'll get...including my undying fraternal love for you. ...Wait but the slightest of instants.
        THIS_DOLL_THAT_JUST_APPEARED_OUT_OF_THIN                                      = 11472,  -- This doll that just appeared out of thin air is called %. It archives your achievements and yours alone, so let's slap your name on it.
        ETERNAL_FLAME_INSCRIBES_YOUR_NAME_UPON_THE_DOLL                               = 11473,  -- Eternal Flame inscribes your name upon the doll in an adorable hand.
        YOU_VE_TAKEN_ETERNAL_FLAME_S_PASSIONATELY_BURNING                             = 11474,  -- You've taken Eternal Flame's passionately burning love deep inside yourself!
        NOW_THAT_YOU_RE_FILLED_WITH_MY_FLAME                                          = 11475,  -- Now that you're filled with my flame of passion, you're ready to spread love and peace all over the land!
        IN_CASE_YOU_DIDN_T_KNOW_YOU_GO                                                = 11476,  -- In case you didn't know, you go about doing this by adding objectives via the Objective List under the Records of Eminence section of the Quests menu.
        THE_WAR_FOR_PEACE_IS_NEVER_ENDING_SO                                          = 11477,  -- The war for peace is never-ending, so there should be some challenges you can repeat indefinitely! Try them all out for as long as your interest holds.
        ONCE_YOU_VE_ACCRUED_ENOUGH_EMINENCE_COME_SEE                                  = 11478,  -- Once you've accrued enough eminence, come see me. I'll give you some rewards...dripping with my love!
        OH_YEAH_ABOUT_THAT                                                            = 11479,  -- Oh, yeah. About that %...
        DOING_THAT_WILL_GET_IT_OUT_OF_YOUR                                            = 11480,  -- ...Doing that will get it out of your hair.
        IT_S_A_BRAND_SPANKING_NEW_MODEL_DEVELOPED                                     = 11481,  -- It's a brand-spanking-new model developed with astral farina or something in mind. It works like the luopans geomancers use.
        UNTIL_WE_MEET_AGAIN_BRAVE_GENT_MAIDEN_WHILE                                   = 11482,  -- Until we meet again, brave gent/maiden]. While you're at it, don't forget to point any peace lovers you see my way. I'm always looking for people to swell my ranks, if you know what I mean.
        A_M_A_N_HAS_BEEN_PULLING_OUT                                                  = 11483,  -- A.M.A.N. has been pulling out all the stops recently, would you not agree? Maybe I should get in tune with this new Records of Eminence thing they have created.
        WHAT_THE_LOVE_AND_PEACE_COALITION_WHY_WOULD                                   = 11484,  -- What? The Love and Peace Coalition? Why would you think that is real for even a moment?
        ETERNAL_FLAME_IS_SIMPLY_LOOKING_FOR_SOMEONE_AT                                = 11485,  -- Eternal Flame is simply looking for someone at whom to talk. None of the locals can stand his absurdities, so he has fallen to preying on unsuspecting pioneers.
        YOU_THERE                                                                     = 11486,  -- You there.
        I_HEARD_FROM_ETERNAL_FLAME_THAT_YOU_ARE                                       = 11487,  -- I heard from Eternal Flame that you are to thank for reuniting his party.
        PERHAPS_YOU_COULD_GIVE_ME_SOME_PEACE_OF                                       = 11488,  -- Perhaps you could give me some peace of mind as well. Would you mind listening to my story?
        LISTEN_TO_HIS_STORY_WHY_NOT_NO_I                                              = 11489,  -- Listen to his story? Why not? No, I can't take any more.
        VERY_WELL_AT_LEAST_ALLOW_ME_TO_SAY                                            = 11490,  -- Very well. At least allow me to say this, however. Thank you for making this dark world a little brighter.
        IT_ALL_STARTED_BACK_WHEN_I_COULD_HARDLY                                       = 11491,  -- It all started back when I could hardly tell a saber from a scimitar.
        I_WAS_ROAMING_THE_WOODS_OF_WEST_RONFAURE                                      = 11492,  -- I was roaming the woods of West Ronfaure when I was ambushed by Orcish reconnaissance. There was no hope for my survival, and I had resigned myself to my fate.
        HOWEVER_BEFORE_THEY_COULD_INFLICT_THE_FINAL_BLOW                              = 11493,  -- However, before they could inflict the final blow upon me, I was blanketed in a comforting light.
        THE_WOUNDS_THAT_RENDERED_ME_NOTHING_MORE_THAN                                 = 11494,  -- The wounds that rendered me nothing more than a bloody hunk of meat closed before my eyes. I felt as if I had the strength to fell a whole horde of Orcs, and succeeded handily in dispatching my aggressors.
        AT_THE_BATTLE_S_CONCLUSION_I_TURNED_TO                                        = 11495,  -- At the battle's conclusion, I turned to face the source of that warm light. What my eyes met with was a certain Tarutaru white mage.
        HER_FACE_SAID_IT_ALL_ALTRUISM_ITSELF_SEEMED                                   = 11496,  -- Her face said it all. Altruism itself seemed to have manifested upon her countenance, and the nonchalant glance she gave froze me in place. I knew my life had changed at that moment.
        I_IMMEDIATELY_DISCARDED_MY_SWORD_AND_HASTENED_TO                              = 11497,  -- I immediately discarded my sword and hastened to Regine's Magicmart, where I outfitted myself in all the trappings of a white mage.
        I_BEGAN_TO_TREAD_THE_PATH_OF_HEALING                                          = 11498,  -- I began to tread the path of healing, determined not only to return the favor she had bestowed upon me, but also to make her recognize my proclivity for the craft.
        ONCE_I_HAD_WHETTED_MY_APPETITE_FOR_THE                                        = 11499,  -- Once I had whetted my appetite for the standard fare of sorcery, I decided to refine my palate by embarking for Castle Oztroja.
        MY_QUEST_TO_SLAY_THOSE_UNHOLY_YAGUDO_ACOLYTES                                 = 11500,  -- My quest to slay those unholy Yagudo acolytes took me deep within the bowels of the heap of dirt and rock they called a castle. While the journey was fraught with many dangers, it was worth it to procure spells the likes of which I had only conceptualized up until then.
        WITH_THIS_MY_ROLE_MODEL_WOULD_BE_UNABLE                                       = 11501,  -- With this, my role model would be unable to deny my puissance. She would shower me with praise that would validate my long excursion and prove how consummate my adoption of the white arts truly was.
        SADLY_THOUGH_THE_TRUTH_IS_A_FICKLE_MISTRESS                                   = 11502,  -- Sadly, though, the truth is a fickle mistress.
        I_LATER_LEARNED_FROM_ETERNAL_FLAME_THAT_OF                                    = 11503,  -- I later learned from Eternal Flame that of all people in Vana'diel...
        THE_VERY_GIRL_WHO_SAVED_MY_LIFE_WAS                                           = 11504,  -- ...the very girl who saved my life was one of his partners in adventure.
        THE_BEACON_OF_LIGHT_WHO_HAD_SHOWN_ME                                          = 11505,  -- The beacon of light who had shown me the way, my raison d'etre...
        THE_TARUTARU_WITH_WHOM_I_WANTED_NOTHING_MORE                                  = 11506,  -- ...the Tarutaru with whom I wanted nothing more than to tell what she meant to me...
        I_WAS_PUSHING_HER_AWAY_FROM_MYSELF_ALL                                        = 11507,  -- ...I was pushing her away from myself all along by working to become the white mage I am today.
        IF_I_HAD_NOT_BEEN_SO_DEVOTED_TO                                               = 11508,  -- If I had not been so devoted to this calling, she would have had more opportunities to join Flame's party and I could have come face-to-face with her.
        I_CURSED_LADY_FORTUNE_HOW_COULD_I_NOT                                         = 11509,  -- I cursed Lady Fortune. How could I not, when my good intentions effectively drove a wedge between me and the dame?
        PERHAPS_I_SHOULD_NOT_DWELL_ON_WHAT_HAS                                        = 11510,  -- Perhaps I should not dwell on what has come to pass, seeing as you have brought a smile to her face once more. I feel as if an incredible weight has been launched from my shoulders into the sky.
        SPEAKING_OF_WHICH_YOU_LIT_THAT_OUKA_RANMAN                                    = 11511,  -- Speaking of which, you lit that ouka ranman in %, did you not?
        MAYBE_I_SHOULD_RETURN_TO_WEST_RONFAURE_AND                                    = 11512,  -- Maybe I should return to West Ronfaure and light my own petals of recollection.
        I_INDEED_MUST_PERFORM_SOME_INTROSPECTION_WHAT_DOES                            = 11513,  -- I indeed must perform some introspection. What does it mean to live as an adventurer? Why do I risk my life every day to be one?
        WHETHER_OR_NOT_I_FIND_ANY_ANSWERS_THERE                                       = 11514,  -- Whether or not I find any answers there, I am greatly indebted to you.
        SHOULD_YOU_EVER_HAVE_THE_OCCASION_TO_VISIT                                    = 11515,  -- Should you ever have the occasion to visit Jeuno, would you do me the favor of seeing how my dear white mage fares?
        ALTANA_TAKE_ME_WHY_IF_N_TISN_T                                                = 11516,  -- Altana take me! Why, if'n 'tisn't mah sweet ol' pum'kin, %!
        WESCOLINA_S_EYES_BEGIN_TO_TWINKLE                                             = 11517,  -- Wescolina's eyes begin to twinkle.
        WELL_AH_LL_BE_A_LEAFKIN_S_UNCLE                                               = 11518,  -- Well, Ah'll be a leafkin's uncle! The day is 'pon us!
        IKHI_DONE_COME_O_ER_HEAH_N_SHOW                                               = 11519,  -- Ikhi done come o'er heah 'n show me that ol' work from the lieberry. Ah can make 'em for you, right as rain!
        WITH_ALL_THOSE_OL_YOU_DONE_BROUGHT_ME                                         = 11520,  -- With all those ol' % you done brought me, should be as simpl' as pluckin' feathers from a heartwing.
        N_WHEN_IT_COMES_TO_CLIPPERS_YOU_CAME                                          = 11521,  -- 'N when it comes to clippers, you came to th' right place, fo' right and fo' true!
        OUR_OR_ER_OF_RENAYE_FRIENDS_HAVE_DONE                                         = 11522,  -- Our Or'er of Renaye friends have done paid mah fee in advance, so all I be needin' 'tis the materials t'emselves.
        I_BE_NEEDIN_THE_RIGHT_AMOUNT_TO_STITCH                                        = 11523,  -- I be needin' the right amount to stitch y'self up a mess o' garments. 'Course, all d'pends on what part you want...
        CHECK_FOR_WHICH_ITEM_HEAD_CHEST_HANDS_LEGS                                    = 11524,  -- Check for which item? Head: %. Chest: %. Hands: %. Legs: %. Feet: % I'm done for now.
        HOO_BOY                                                                       = 11525,  -- Hoo boy, %?
        LEMME_JUS_PUT_ON_MAH_THINKIN_BONNET_YES                                       = 11526,  -- Lemme jus' put on mah thinkin' bonnet... Yes, I be needin' %, 'course, in addition to % and %. Yuppers, if'n you could bring those to me that'd be th' bee's knees!
        BUT_AH_KNOW_THAT_YOU_RE_BUSIER_THAN                                           = 11527,  -- But Ah know that you're busier than an alley cat durin' matin' season, so Ah can spot you some o' the materials.
        SO_IF_N_YOU_JUST_GIMME_THE_MOST                                               = 11528,  -- So if'n you just gimme the most important parts--% and %--together with # bayld, I should be able to handle things from theah.
        CRIMINY_I_SWEAH_NEXT_TIME_AROUND_YOU_LL                                       = 11529,  -- Criminy, %! I sweah, next time around you'll have me sewin' your unduhgahments!
        HOO_HOO_I_BE_TICKLIN_MY_FUNNY_BONE                                            = 11530,  -- Hoo hoo, I be ticklin' my funny bone!
        BUT_IN_THE_NAME_O_OL_ZACARIAH_I                                               = 11531,  -- But in the name o' ol' Zacariah, I promise that you'll have clothin' fittin' of one attuned with nature!
        POSITIVELY_WUNN_FUL_I_TRUST_YOU_HAVE_TH                                       = 11532,  -- Positively wunn'ful, %! I trust you have th' items Ah need for your %?
        HAVE_WECOLINA_CREATE_YOUR_GARMENT_BY_THE_GODDESS                              = 11533,  -- Have Wecolina create your garment? By the Goddess, yes! No...stop talking.
        WELL_SLAP_MAH_BUM_N_CALL_ME_SHIRLEY                                           = 11534,  -- Well, slap mah bum 'n call me Shirley, you do! Ready to have me lovin'ly stitch together your % for # bayld in place 'o th' othah materials?
        PAY_THE_PRICE_YOU_HAVE_BAYLD_BAYLD_ABSOLUTELY                                 = 11535,  -- Pay the price? (You have # bayld). # bayld? Absolutely, Shirley. No. Haven't I suffered enough?
        BUT_DARLIN_WE_VE_BARELY_GOTTEN_STARTED                                        = 11536,  -- But darlin', we've barely gotten started!
        RIGHT_THESE_FINGERS_RE_JUS_ITCHIN_TO_GET                                      = 11537,  -- Right! These fingers're jus' itchin' to get down to work!
        HON_YOU_DON_HAVE_NOUGH_BAYLD                                                  = 11538,  -- Hon, you don' have 'nough bayld.
        WHY_YOU_JUST_BEAM_DOWN_ON_ME_LIKE                                             = 11539,  -- Why, you just beam down on me like sunshine from th' heavens, don' you, %? Ah'm so glad to see you, because Ah've jus' finished your %! A fine piece o' work, if'n Ah do say so m'self.
        THE_AH_USED_FOR_THE_WEAVE_IS_SAID                                             = 11540,  -- The % Ah used for the weave is said to focus the wearer's mental acuity--that's the fancy words for noggin power. What's more 'tis both functional 'n stylish!
        ALL_TH_ENERGY_CONTAINED_IN_THE_REALLY_DREW                                    = 11541,  -- All th' energy contained in the % really drew forth the potential of this heah piece.
        SURE_GETS_STICKY_OUT_THEAH_IN_ULBUKA_NO                                       = 11542,  -- Sure gets sticky out theah in Ulbuka, no? That's why I wanted you to brin' me that %. Very breathable material that lets both air 'n magic through!
        Y_KNOW_WHY_AH_ASKED_FOR_AIN_T                                                 = 11543,  -- Y'know why Ah asked for %? Ain't nothin' brimming with more geomantic potential, that's why! Ah used some ol' sewing techniques passed down from th' eastern lands.
        DID_YA_KNOW_THAT_ARE_USED_TO_REDUCE                                           = 11544,  -- Did ya know that % are used to reduce wear 'n tear on your luopan? Mah mah, sir/ma'am], Ah do declare that you done learn' somethin' new today!
        HEAH_YOU_GO_DUMPLIN                                                           = 11545,  -- Heah you go, dumplin'!
        WELL_YOU_DONE_LOOK_TH_HAN_SOMES_PURTIES                                       = 11546,  -- Well, you done look th' han'somes'/purties'] thing I ever did see. Now go out theah and do me proud!
        HEY_IF_YOU_KEEP_LOITERING_AROUND_MY_PROPERTY                                  = 11547,  -- Hey, if you keep loitering around my property, I'm going to personally-wersonally take you down to the Waterways and feed you to--
        IF_YOU_KEEP_LOITERING_AROUND_MY_PROPERTY_I                                    = 11548,  -- %! If you keep loitering around my property, I'm going to personally-wersonally take you down to the Waterways and feed you to--
        AHHH_YOU_MUST_BE_ONE_OF_THE_TEST                                              = 11549,  -- Ahhh, you must be one of the test subjectarus for our new insto-disemboweler. Come right this way.
        WHAT_YOU_RE_HERE_ABOUT_RUNE_FENCER_EQUIPMENTARU                               = 11550,  -- What? You're here about rune fencer equipmentaru?
        WE_VE_GIVEN_OVER_THE_REIN_WEINS_FOR                                           = 11551,  -- We've given over the rein-weins for that to Octavien. You're better off asking him directly.
        LET_S_SEE_THIS_DISSERTATION_WATION_OF_YOURS                                   = 11552,  -- Let's see this dissertation-wation of yours. Wait, this is just a copy of %. Everything written in here's common sense by now.
        HUH_WHY_WOULD_I_BOTHER_EXTRICATARUING_THE_FIRST                               = 11553,  -- Huh? Why would I bother extricataruing the first letter of each line and then reading them backwards?
        WELL_I_STAND_CORRECTARUED_IT_APPEARS_THAT_THE                                 = 11554,  -- ...Well, I stand correctarued. It appears that the author embedded instructions for something in this document.
        APPLY_AN_ASTRAL_PATINA_TO_CERTAIN_SECTIONS_ENGRAVE                            = 11555,  -- Apply an astral patina to certain sections... Engrave arcane glyptics of the opposing affinity... Impressive-wessive.
        IT_GOES_ON_TO_MENTION_UTILIZING_THE_POWER                                     = 11556,  -- It goes on to mention utilizing the power of otherworldly stones to create a special form of embroidery-- Why, this is revolutionary!
        I_ONCE_TRIED_MANUFACTURING_A_NEW_TYPE_OF                                      = 11557,  -- I once tried manufacturing a new type of protective fabric, but had long since abandoned the idea. With this new process, though, all I'd need is % to restartaru my efforts!
        FROM_WHAT_I_VE_HEARD_YOU_MUST_VENTURE                                         = 11558,  -- From what I've heard, you must venture deep within Kamihr Drifts to an ominous bulwark. If you're able to pass through it, the curio-wurio should be all yours.
        AS_FOR_WHAT_HORRORS_LIE_TEEMING_BEHIND_IT                                     = 11559,  -- As for what horrors lie teeming behind it, I haven't the foggiestaru.
        AT_ANY_RATE_YOU_RE_THE_PIONEER_IT                                             = 11560,  -- At any rate, you're the pioneer. It's your prerogative-wogative whether or not you go there. All I'm saying is that it would be nice if you helped advance our coalition's cause...and by extension, your own.
        IN_THE_EVENTARU_YOU_DO_END_UP_GETTING                                         = 11561,  -- In the eventaru you do end up getting ahold of %, take it to Yestin-Ovestin. I'll tell him to expect you.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_LEAVE_ME_ALONE_AND                                                = 11562,  -- Oh, it's you. Leave me alone and get lostaru!
        NOW_WE_RE_TALKING_I_THOUGHT_I_D                                               = 11563,  -- Now we're talking. I thought I'd have to sitaru through a bunch of small talk and begging before getting down to business-wusiness.
        AMCHUCHU_FINALLY_TOOK_OFF_HER_KID_GLOVE_WOVES                                 = 11564,  -- Amchuchu finally took off her kid glove-woves and gave me a copy of %, but never did I think that I'd be able to lay eyes on %.
        I_SUPPOSE_THIS_IS_AN_OFFER_I_CAN                                              = 11565,  -- I suppose this is an offer I can't refuse-wuse, seeing as how you've already done the dirty work.
        AS_FOR_PAYMENT_DON_T_WORRY_THE_INVENTORS                                      = 11566,  -- As for payment, don't worry. The Inventors' Coalition has already forked over more than the likes of you could afford. Just bring me the requisitaru materials.
        YOU_TELL_ME_THE_ARMOR_I_TELL_YOU                                              = 11567,  -- You tell me the armor, I tell you what materials to bring so I can craftaru it, and you go get them. No backtalk, snide remarks, or unnecessary questions from you.
        WHAT_PIECE_OF_ARMOR_HEAD_BODY_HANDS_LEGS                                      = 11568,  -- What piece of armor? Head: %. Body: %. Hands: %. Legs: %. Feet: %. None. I'm done.
        YOU_WANT_HUH_IF_THAT_S_THE_CASE                                               = 11569,  -- You want %, huh? If that's the case...
        THERE_S_NO_NEGOTIATARUING_THE_HOWEVER_THE_AND                                 = 11570,  -- There's no negotiataruing the %. However, the % and % we can work with. And none of this one-by-one stuff, either. Gimme them all at once.
        IF_YOU_RE_TOO_LAZY_TO_BOTHER_GETTING                                          = 11571,  -- If you're too lazy to bother getting the last two materials, feel free to skip them...as long as you have enough bayld-wayld.
        JUST_SO_YOU_DON_T_COME_DISTURBING_WURBING                                     = 11572,  -- Just so you don't come disturbing-wurbing me in the middle of more important things, let me spell it out for you. Have # bayld on hand if you only bring % and %.
        I_CAN_T_WAIT_TO_BE_THE_FIRSTARU                                               = 11573,  -- I can't wait to be the firstaru person in known history to forge these pieces. Look, my legs are tremble-wembling in anticipation!
