        YOUR_OPPONENT_S_TOTAL_YOUR_TOTAL                                              = 12201,  -- Your opponent's total: #[/ (Bust!)] Your total: #[/ (Bust!)] [You win, and thus have the right to gloat all you want until your rematch./Don't go throwing your dice just because you lost, all right?/You are equally matched, and have drawn.]
        CLEAR_YOUR_MIND_AND_READY_YOUR_CHRONOLOGICAL_SENSES                           = 12202,  -- Clear your mind and ready your chronological senses, for this amusement pits you against time's dilatory creep. The objective here's to speak to me a certain amount of times at the intervals I tell you.
        JUST_SO_YOU_KNOW_I_LL_ONLY_GIVE                                               = 12203,  -- Just so you know, I'll only give you the length of time to wait and how far off you were from the specified interval when spoken to. Furthermore, the difference between your guess and the answer is cumulative.
        IF_YOU_RE_TOO_SLOW_ONE_ROUND_YOU                                              = 12204,  -- If you're too slow one round, you can make up time by being a little fast the next.
        FINALLY_YOU_CLAIM_VICTORY_BY_STAYING_WITHIN_A                                 = 12205,  -- Finally, you claim victory by staying within a certain number of seconds by the end of the final round. I hope this cleared things up, and enjoy honing your mastery over Father Time.
        I_TAKE_IT_THAT_MEANS_YOU_RE_IN                                                = 12206,  -- I take it that means you're in the correct state of mind to challenge the forces of time. Let's do this!
