        IT_S_JUDGMENT_TIME_YOU_WERE_SECOND                                            = 12209,  -- It's judgment time! You were [a total of /a total of /]# second[/s] [early./late./off. In other words, perfectly on-target!] [It seems that the concept of time eludes you./Congratulations, you've temporarily mastered the forces of time!]
        A_WET_AND_WILD_ADVENTURE_THIS_YOU_AND                                         = 12210,  -- A wet and wild adventure, this. You and I take turns filling a goblet with water until the cup runneth over, with the offending competitor sent to drown in shame.
        THE_RUB_IS_THAT_IT_LOOKS_AS_IF                                                = 12211,  -- The rub is that it looks as if there is more water in the goblet than actually exists. Thus you will need to exercise the entirety of your patience and perspicacity to wrench victory from my clutches.
        AS_IF_THAT_WERE_NOT_ENOUGH_I_HAVE                                             = 12212,  -- As if that were not enough, I have added an extra layer of frustration by granting us competitors certain abilities dubbed afflictions and remedies.
        ON_THE_ONE_HAND_AFFLICTIONS_ALLOW_YOU_TO                                      = 12213,  -- On the one hand, afflictions allow you to do such things as change the amount of water I see.
        YOU_CAN_ALSO_USE_THEM_TO_NEGATE_THE                                           = 12214,  -- You can also use them to negate the effects of my remedies or limit the amount of water I can pour.
        ON_THE_OTHER_HAND_REMEDIES_HELP_INCREASE_OR                                   = 12215,  -- On the other hand, remedies help increase or decrease either the amount of the water you can pour or the amount of water in the goblet. As a final twist, they can also negate the effects of afflictions.
        AFFLICTIONS_AND_REMEDIES_CAUSE_THE_TIDES_OF_COMPETITION                       = 12216,  -- Afflictions and remedies cause the tides of competition to surge and swell to an extreme degree, so we restrict their use to once per game. Be prudent with which you use and when.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_POUR_AWAY_USE_AN                                             = 12217,  -- What will you do? Pour away! Use an affliction. Use a remedy. Throw in the towel.
        HOW_WILL_YOU_AFFLICT_YOUR_OPPONENT_I_WON                                      = 12218,  -- How will you afflict your opponent? I won't, that's how. Increase amount poured. Decrease amount poured. Fabricate water level. Remove a remedy. Restrict to greater pouring options. Restrict to lesser pouring options.
        WHAT_REMEDY_WILL_YOU_USE_NONE_THAT_S                                          = 12219,  -- What remedy will you use? None, that's what! Increase amount poured. Decrease amount poured. Cure an affliction. Increase maximum water level. Decrease maximum water level.
        POUR_HOW_MUCH_CURRENTLY_ONZ_ONE_ONZ_TWO                                       = 12220,  -- Pour how much? (Currently # onz[/es].) One onz. Two onzes. Three onzes. Four onzes. Five onzes.
