        HOW_MAY_I_BE_OF_SERVICE_TODAY                                                 = 12498,  -- How may I be of service today?
        WHAT_TO_DO_NOTHING_VIEW_LIST_OF_STORABLE                                      = 12499,  -- What to do... Nothing. View list of storable armor sets. Have stored armor returned.
        WE_ARE_CURRENTLY_OFFERING_STORAGE_SERVICE_FOR_THE                             = 12500,  -- We are currently offering storage service for the following armor sets:
        LET_ME_SEE_AH_YES_LORD_LADY_WE                                                = 12501,  -- Let me see... Ah yes, Lord/Lady] %. We are currently holding the following garments...
        NONE_LEVEL_24_30_ARMOR_LEVEL_31_40                                            = 12502,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set from storage?] None. Level 24`30 armor. Level 31`40 armor. Level 41`50 armor. Artifact armor/High level gear. Relic armor.
        NONE_IRON_CHAINMAIL_SHADE_HARNESS_BRASS_SCALE_ARMOR                           = 12503,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Iron Chainmail. Shade Harness. Brass Scale Armor. Wool Robe. Eisenplatte Armor. Soil Gi. Seer's Tunic. Studded Armor. Centurion's Scale Mail. Mercenary Captain's Doublet. Garish Tunic. Noct Doublet.
        NONE_CUSTOM_ARMOR_HUME_MALE_CUSTOM_ARMOR_HUME                                 = 12504,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Custom Armor (Hume Male). Custom Armor (Hume Female). Magna Armor (Elvaan Male). Magna Armor (Elvaan Female). Wonder Armor (Tarutaru). Savage Armor (Mithra). Elder Armor (Galka). Linen Cloak. Padded Armor. Silver Chainmail. Gambison. Iron Scale Armor. Cuir Armor. Velvet Robe. Opaline Dress. Royal Squire's Chainmail. Plate Armor. Combat Caster's Cloak. Argent Attire.
        NONE_ALUMINE_HAUBERT_CARAPACE_ARMOR_BANDED_MAIL_HARA                          = 12505,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Alumine Haubert. Carapace Armor. Banded Mail. Hara-Ate. Raptor Armor. Steel Scale Armor. Wool Gambison. Shinobi Gi. Mythril Plate Armor. Iron Musketeer's Cuirass. Tactician Magician's Cloak. White Cloak. Austere Robe. Crow Jupon.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS                                  = 12506,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_2                                = 12507,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_3                                = 12508,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_4                                = 12509,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, and %.
        A_STORAGE_FEE_OF_GIL_WILL_BE_REQUIRED                                         = 12510,  -- A storage fee of # gil will be required upon pickup of this particular set.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_FIGHTER_S_ARMOR_TEMPLE                                      = 12511,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Fighter's Armor. Temple Attire. Healer's Attire. Wizard's Attire. Warlock's Armor. Rogue's Attire. Gallant Armor. Chaos Armor. Beast Armor. Choral Attire. Hunter's Attire. Myochin Armor. Ninja Garb. Drachen Armor. Evoker's Attire. Magus Attire. Corsair's Attire. Puppetry Attire. Dancer's Attire. Dancer's Attire. Scholar's Attire. Amir Armor Set. Pahluwan Armor Set. Yigit Armor Set.
        THE_STORAGE_FEE_FOR_YOUR_ARMOR_COMES_TO                                       = 12512,  -- The storage fee for your armor comes to # gil.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PAY_THE_FEE_NOT                                                = 12513,  -- Do you wish to pay the fee? Not at this time. Yes.
        I_AM_SORRY_SIR_MA_AM_GIL_IS                                                   = 12514,  -- I am sorry, sir/ma'am]. # gil is required before we can return your armor.
        VERY_WELL_SIR_MA_AM_WHEN_YOU_WISH                                             = 12515,  -- Very well, sir/ma'am]. When you wish to have your armor returned, remember to present this claim slip along with the #-gil storage fee at any of our five convenient pickup locations around Vana'diel.
        REGULATIONS_DO_NOT_ALLOW_ADVENTURERS_TO_STORE_MORE                            = 12516,  -- Regulations do not allow adventurers to store more than one set of the same armor.
        THE_ITEMS_YOU_ATTEMPTED_TO_TRADE_HAVE_BEEN                                    = 12517,  -- The items you attempted to trade have been returned.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_WARRIOR_S_ARMOR_MELEE                                       = 12518,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Warrior's Armor. Melee Attire. Cleric's Attire. Sorcerer's Attire. Duelist's Armor. Assassin's Attire. Valor Armor. Abyss Armor. Monster Armor. Bard's Attire. Scout's Attire. Saotome Armor. Koga Garb. Wyrm Armor. Summoner's Attire. Mirage Attire. Commodore Attire. Pantin Attire. Etoile Attire. Argute Attire.
        IF_IT_S_A_SMITH_YOU_SEEK_THE                                                  = 12519,  -- If it's a smith you seek, the only one that comes to my mind is Yestin-Ovestin.
        HE_NEVER_SEEMS_TO_ACCEPT_WORK_FROM_ANYONE                                     = 12520,  -- He never seems to accept work from anyone, so you can always find him waddling around the waterfront. The only thing you're apt to get from him is a wad of spit in the eye, but you never know.
        INNOVATIONS_THAT_ARE_FUN_FOR_THE_WHOLE_FAMILY_2                               = 12521,  -- Innovations that are fun for the whole family, safe and reliable services, and not a hint of blood money anywhere! That's the Inventors' Coalition in a nutshell.
        GLOBULES_OF_SLAG_AND_VARIOUS_BITS_OF_STRING                                   = 12522,  -- Globules of slag and various bits of string lay strewn about haphazardly...
        FOR_THE_LASTARU_TIME_I_DON_T_GIVE                                             = 12523,  -- For the lastaru time, I don't give a damn about behemoth horn aphro...oh.
        SO_YOU_RE_THE_SERVANTARU_OCTAVIEN_SAID_HE                                     = 12524,  -- So you're the servantaru Octavien said he was going to send...
        YOU_NEED_ME_TO_FORGEY_WORGE_A_BLADE                                           = 12525,  -- You need me to forgey-worge a blade for you, then?
        IS_THAT_WHAT_YOU_CAME_HERE_TO_ASK                                             = 12526,  -- Is that what you came here to ask? Yes, it is. No, it's not.
        THEN_WHY_THE_HELL_DID_YOU_COME_HERE                                           = 12527,  -- Then why the hell did you come here? Wait, don't answer that. Just make like a log and splitaru.
        WELL_TOUGH_TROLL_TEATS                                                        = 12528,  -- Well, tough troll teats.
        THE_ORDER_OF_ORVAIL_WANTS_A_SWORD_THAT                                        = 12529,  -- The Order of Orvail wants a sword that is normally produced using techniques that died out centuries-wenturies ago. The ones in which we contemporary blacksmiths are versed are barely applicable.
        IF_I_ADD_EVEN_THE_SLIGHTARUEST_BIT_TOO                                        = 12530,  -- If I add even the slightaruest bit too much or too little of certain ingredients after smelting, the blade will turn out duller than that intolerable geomancer Sylvie.
        SABERS_BROADSWORDS_RAPIERS_THEY_RE_ALL_LIVING_BREATHING                       = 12531,  -- Sabers, broadswords, rapiers, they're all living, breathing things...and they all feed off their forgers' souls. Your attitudes and intentions when imbuing-wuing the steel are absorbed and determine its personality--for bettaru or worse.
        SOMEONE_AS_ADEPTARU_AT_SMITHING_AS_ME_CAN                                     = 12532,  -- Someone as adeptaru at smithing as me can bring this sword to life in exchange for shortening my own. The real problem, however, is getting the materials-werials together.
        I_HAVE_THE_REQUISITARU_METALS_AND_LEATHER_BUT                                 = 12533,  -- I have the requisitaru metals and leather, but for a weapon as mountainous-wountainous as this, you'll need to venture forth into the heart of Ulbuka's darkness to find some exceptionally powerful resources.
        I_DON_T_HAVE_EITHER_OR_BUT_THEY                                               = 12534,  -- I don't have either % or %, but they're both indispensable-wensable.
        I_VE_HEARD_YOU_CAN_FIND_IN_BUT                                                = 12535,  -- I've heard you can find % in %, but I've certainly never been there. It's no stroll past the statue of the Goddess-woddess with your lover, and only those either blinded by fame and fortune or seeking the sweet reprieve of eternal slumber-wumber ever set out for it.
        I_MAY_SHAPE_SWORDS_FOR_A_LIVING_BUT                                           = 12536,  -- I may shape swords for a living, but I wouldn't be caughtaru dead swinging one. There's no way I'm going out there.
        GO_BACK_TO_WHATEVER_GODDESSFORSAKEN_CONTINENTARU_YOU_CAME                     = 12537,  -- Go back to whatever Goddessforsaken continentaru you came from and forget about that sword.
        ATTACHED_TO_THE_BARREL_IS_A_NOTE_WRITTEN                                      = 12538,  -- Attached to the barrel is a note, written in a strong and decisive hand, that reads thus:
        DON_T_ASK_ME_TO_MAKE_WAKE_ANYTHING                                            = 12539,  -- Don't ask me to make-wake anything right now. Go the hell away. --Yestin-Ovestin
        BY_THE_GODDESS_ALMIGHTY_WIGHTY_TH_THIS_IS                                     = 12540,  -- By the Goddess almighty-wighty, th-this is...%! So, you were truly able to bestaru that apparition...
        AND_YOU_EVEN_MANAGED_TO_GET_AHOLD_OF                                          = 12541,  -- And you even managed to get ahold of %?
        INCONCEIVABLE_WEIVABLE_IT_D_TAKE_MILLENNIA_FOR_THE                            = 12542,  -- Inconceivable-weivable! It'd take millennia for the stars to align as they have for you! You must've used some sort of pioneer trickery.
        AH_JERRA_BUT_IF_SHE_WAS_WILLING_TO                                            = 12543,  -- Ah...Jerra. But if she was willing to partaru with it, that must mean...you're one of the elite who're engraved with the %.
        I_WOULDN_T_WANT_TO_DISAPPOINTARU_SOMEONE_AS                                   = 12544,  -- I wouldn't want to disappointaru someone as devoted to swinging swords as I am to smithing them. Just let me gather-wather myself.
        FIRST_I_MUST_EXPUNGE_ALL_THE_CONFLICTARUING_THOUGHTS                          = 12545,  -- First, I must expunge all the conflictaruing thoughts from my mind.
        THERE_I_M_NOW_IN_THE_CORRECTARU_STATE                                         = 12546,  -- ...There. I'm now in the correctaru state of mind to receive your % and %. Thank you.
        OHO_I_CAN_FEEL_THE_FIRE_OF_THE                                                = 12547,  -- Oho, I can feel the fire of the forge burning-wurning passionately within me once again!
        A_RHYTHMICAL_CLANKING_CAN_BE_HEARD_FROM_WITHIN                                = 12548,  -- A rhythmical clanking can be heard from within, mixed with the concentrated mumblings of a craftsman deep in thought.
        WHY_D_YOU_HAVE_TO_MAKE_THIS_SO                                                = 12549,  -- Why'd you have to make this so heavy? I feel like it's going to rrrip my arms from their sockets!
        I_LL_RRRIP_YOUR_ARMS_OFF_MYSELF_IF                                            = 12550,  -- I'll rrrip your arms off myself if you insultaru my masterpiece again!
        SIR_MADAM_I_VE_ORDERED_THE_COURIERS_COALITION                                 = 12551,  -- Sir/Madam] %, I've ordered the Couriers' Coalition to deliver the sword to Octavien postaru-haste. --Yestin-Ovestin
        OH_IT_S_YOU_GIVE_ME_A_MINUTARU                                                = 12552,  -- Oh, it's you. Give me a minutaru and I'll get that equipment Octavien ordered for--
        THAT_S_NOT_WHAT_I_THINK_WINK_IT                                               = 12553,  -- That's not what I think-wink it is, is it!?
        IT_IS_NEVER_IN_MY_WILDESTARU_DREAMS_DID                                       = 12554,  -- It is! Never in my wildestaru dreams did I ever think I'd get a chance to read the fabled-wabled %.
        GIMME_WIMME_THAT                                                              = 12555,  -- Gimme-wimme that.
        MUMBLE_AHHH_I_SEE_MUMBLE_OF_COURSE_HOW                                        = 12556,  -- <Mumble> Ahhh, I see... <Mumble> Of course! How could I be so stupid!?
        UNBELIEVABLE_APPLYING_THESE_TECHNIQUES_TO_YOUR_EQUIPMENTARU_WILL              = 12557,  -- Unbelievable... Applying these techniques to your equipmentaru will increase your defenses against any malady!
        SORRY_BUT_I_LL_NEED_TO_ALTER_MY                                               = 12558,  -- Sorry, but I'll need to alter my designs a bit. I can't in good conscience-wonscience give it to you like this.
        THERE_S_NO_WAY_I_COULD_LIVE_WITH                                              = 12559,  -- There's no way I could live with myself if I gave this to you in its currentaru state. This calls for some alterations.
